{"id": "41609", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41609", "title": "Cult of Damnation", "text": "The Cult of Damnation is a cult that worships the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThe cult was formed by Skarn, who formed it in the aftermath of the destruction of the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;. In just a few years, Skarn gained a massive cult of followers, who tempted and decieved to swell their ranks among the &lt;a href=\"Western%20Kingdoms\"&gt;Western Kingdoms&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, the cult attacked the village of &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt;, abducting a number of its townsfolk for sacrifice. Furthermore, having obtained a &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; shard, they attempted to summon Skarn into &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. However, their efforts were thwarted by &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis wasn't the last of the cult however, as round about the same time, more of their members were searching the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt; for the Worldstone shard that had impacted the woods. They came into conflict with the &lt;a href=\"Bloodsworn\"&gt;Bloodsworn&lt;/a&gt;, whose &lt;a href=\"the%20Countess\"&gt;leader&lt;/a&gt; owned the shard. &lt;a href=\"Lakrii\"&gt;Lakrii&lt;/a&gt; refused &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;'s ultimatum to turn over the shard to the cult, which resulted in the two cult groups battling each other in the forest.\nLater, the Cult gathered at &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;. This caught the attention of &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, which offered &lt;a href=\"bounties\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s to deal with them.\nIn-game.\nThe Cult of Damnation is an enemy faction in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is encountered primarily in Wortham, as part of the game's tutorial. It is briefly encountered again in the Dark Wood, but the Bloodsworn are the primary enemy in this zone. The Cult is later encountered at &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;.\nKnown Members.\nCommanders.\nThe following are listed in terms of apparent hierarchy within the Cult:"}
{"id": "53079", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53079", "title": "Cult of Hatred", "text": "The is a cult associated with &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe features in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", in the elite quest \"\"&lt;a href=\"Tempered%20Instinct\"&gt;Tempered Instinct&lt;/a&gt;\"\""}
{"id": "44348", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44348", "title": "Cult of Terror", "text": "The Cult of Terror is a cult loyal to &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nStormpoint.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, they attacked the island of &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt; in a bid to retrieve the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; shard that had impacted the island &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231265\"&gt;seven years prior&lt;/a&gt;. As they didn't know the shard's exact location, they attacked and destroyed &lt;a href=\"the%20Shanties\"&gt;the Shanties&lt;/a&gt;.\nOf the survivors, some they took for sacrifice, others they interrogated for information concerning the shard's location. Captives that gave displeasing information were killed and &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haruspex%7Chad\"&gt;their entrails read&lt;/a&gt; They conducted human sacrifices in order to summon &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s.\nAfterwards, they besieged &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint%20Keep\"&gt;Stormpoint Keep&lt;/a&gt;, in a bid to retrieve the Worldstone shard that resided within.. Corpses of the sacrificed were gathered at &lt;a href=\"Windswept%20Shoals\"&gt;different&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"the%20Shanties\"&gt;parts&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Barbican%20Transverse\"&gt;of&lt;/a&gt; Stormpoint in grotesque piles that they referred to as \"sculptor's piles\". This binds the &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s of the victims to the piles. These souls were used by the Cultists to \"sharpen their blades\".\nThe Cult succeeded in obtaining the shard and retreated from Stormpoint.\nAncients' Cradle.\nThey were unable to send the shard to Diablo because of &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;'s taint within it. In order to purify the shard, they set sail on the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Sea\"&gt;Forgotten Sea&lt;/a&gt; in search of the &lt;a href=\"Ancients%27%20Cradle\"&gt;Ancients' Cradle&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt the Cradle, the cult tried to harness the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20of%20Life\"&gt;power flowing through the land&lt;/a&gt;, but were rejected violently. The backlash killed some cultists, and reanimated them to fight the intruders.\nThey then rampaged through &lt;a href=\"the%20Granges\"&gt;the nearby farmlands&lt;/a&gt;, killing people and interrogating anyone who looked to be of importance. When it bore no fruit, they headed deeper into the island to &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Unholy%20Nativity\"&gt;the nearest place of importance&lt;/a&gt; to interrogate the officials there.\nDark Rebirth.\nWith the purified shard in hand, the cult arrived at &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;Tristram Cathedral&lt;/a&gt;, the place where Diablo once rose. Their plan was to use powerful imprints of Diablo to perform a ritual that would open a path to their master. The strongest imprints were &lt;a href=\"Albrecht\"&gt;Albrecht&lt;/a&gt;, (Diablo's former host), and &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;Tristram Cathedral&lt;/a&gt; (Diablo's former lair). Unfortunately, when they tried to implant the shard in his &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt; he instead turned into a raging monster. With the proof of concept, they tried infecting other corpses (and some hapless civilians) with the shard, creating more &lt;a href=\"Shardborne\"&gt;Shardborne&lt;/a&gt; in the process. During this time, the Bride of Hell led a regiment of cultists to &lt;a href=\"Leoric%27s%20Manor\"&gt;Leoric's Manor&lt;/a&gt; in search of any object in which an imprint of Diablo still lingered.\nAlbrecht was still their link to Diablo, only if they could bring him to heel. After &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; defeated Albrecht, the &lt;a href=\"Bride%20of%20Hell\"&gt;Bride of Hell&lt;/a&gt; connected the Shard to his dying psyche, creating a &lt;a href=\"Path%20of%20Memories\"&gt;temporary realm out of his memories&lt;/a&gt;. Within Albrecht's mind, the Bride of Hell goes to the point with the strongest imprint of Diablo \u2014 when Albrecht became possessed. Using the imprint, she created a portal directly to Diablo in &lt;a href=\"Skarn%27s%20Throne\"&gt;Skarn's Throne&lt;/a&gt; room.\nThere, the shard is delivered to Diablo, who attunes himself to it in order to speed up his &lt;a href=\"resurrection\"&gt;resurrection&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Cult of Terror is introduced in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", in the \"&lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt;\" questline. Its bestiary is a mix of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; enemies, though all of its members are classified as demons within the game."}
