{"id": "6793", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6793", "title": "Culwen's Point", "text": "Culwen's Point is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"War%20Sword\"&gt;War Sword&lt;/a&gt; from \"\".\nCulwen's Point is one of the first unique &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;swords&lt;/a&gt; to give a bonus to all skills, although it is a minimal bonus. Beside this skill boost, Culwen's Point actually has few notable properties.\nMost of the advantages of Culwen's Point are indirect, rather than directly correlated to damage. Its increased &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt;, when combined with its increase &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Rating\"&gt;Attack Rating&lt;/a&gt;, may make Culwen's Point simply land more hits and deal more damage than other weapons, assuming that a wielder of Culwen's Point has high enough &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;. \nAdditionally, Culwen's Point also has some useful defensive bonuses. It reduces the length of &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; by 50%. This may be particularly useful against bosses such as &lt;a href=\"Andariel\"&gt;Andariel&lt;/a&gt;, or enemies like &lt;a href=\"Mummy\"&gt;Mummies&lt;/a&gt;. \nCulwen's Point also gives its user a &lt;a href=\"Faster%20Hit%20Recovery\"&gt;Faster Hit Recovery&lt;/a&gt;. Although not going so far as to decrease damage, this would give a physical fighter more time to recover from hits and strike back with their own, generally giving them the upper hand in a one-on-one battle, or preventing them from being deadlocked when surrounded by hordes of enemies.\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: (13-14) To (34-36) \nRequired Level: 29\nRequired Strength: 71\nRequired Dexterity: 45\nDurability: 44\nSword Class - "}
