{"id": "43204", "revid": "27473235", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43204", "title": "Curse of the Scepter", "text": "Curse of the Scepter is an &lt;a href=\"elite%20quest\"&gt;elite quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"\nDescription.\nIntroduction.\n\"Shortly after recovering the &lt;a href=\"Scepter%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;Scepter of Fahir&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tabri\"&gt;Tabri&lt;/a&gt;, leader of the &lt;a href=\"Amber%20Blades\"&gt;Amber Blades&lt;/a&gt;, went missing in the dead of night. The &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;desert's&lt;/a&gt; two big gangs--the Amber Blades and the &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Scorpions\"&gt;Sand Scorpions&lt;/a&gt;--are converging on the buried &lt;a href=\"Library%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Library of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. If Tabri and the scepter are on the move, perhaps a new ruler of Shassar is about to begin their reign.\"\nStages.\n\"No one in the Amber Blades keeps their ear to the ground more than &lt;a href=\"Zov\"&gt;Zov&lt;/a&gt;. Find him in the Library, and Tabri's whereabouts will become clearer.\"\n\"Convinced Tabri has fled &lt;a href=\"Vataos\"&gt;Vataos&lt;/a&gt;'s wrath and is hiding somewhere in the Library, &lt;a href=\"Zov\"&gt;Zov&lt;/a&gt; suggests you join him in his search for her. She cannot have gone far!\"\n\"Separated from you, Zov has quickly found himself in trouble. Rescue him from &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Aberration\"&gt;horrifying experiments&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n\"This place is far from a safe place for discussion and Tabri is nowhere to be found. Best to leave the area.\"\n\"The search for Tabri and the Scepter of Fahir continues. It seems Zov and &lt;a href=\"Peth\"&gt;Peth&lt;/a&gt; have joined forces with &lt;a href=\"the%20Curator\"&gt;the Curator&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"golem\"&gt;golem&lt;/a&gt;s.\"\n\"You have been handed over a &lt;a href=\"Tabri%27s%20Letter\"&gt;letter&lt;/a&gt; from Tabri intended for Peth. Read through its contents and speak with Zov.\"\n\"Zov isn't exactly wrong. Zoltun Kulle's &lt;a href=\"golem\"&gt;creations&lt;/a&gt; in the hands of the Sand Scorpions could lead to warfare, or even worse outcomes. Perhaps you should join Zov in his search.\"\n\"Following after Zov, you reach a forgotten chamber in the depths of the Library. What strange artifacts could possibly lie in wait here?\"\n\"Exactly as you predicted, Zov's impatience has cost him. Hold back the &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; hordes until you can discover a way to free him.\"\n\"With the undead &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; defeated, you can finally free Zov. If he stops squirming, that is.\"\n\"Freed from the machine, Zov seems no worse for wear. Perhaps now he will be more considerate of your warnings.\"\n\"Once more, the search continues. Best to keep an eye out for Zov as you explore the Library. Who knows where he might turn up.\"\n\"At long last, Zov seems to finally be on Tabri's trail. Search the area for clues to her whereabouts.\"\n\"The scattered parchment and papers indicate this area served as Zoltun Kulle's experiments in &lt;a href=\"teleport\"&gt;teleport&lt;/a&gt;ation. Could Tabri have taken one of those portals?\"\n\"Following Zov, you reach a portal much larger than the others. This must be where Tabri has taken refuge. Follow after her before &lt;a href=\"Vataos\"&gt;Vataos&lt;/a&gt; and his men arrive.\"\n\"The portal is sealed, leaving Tabri and whatever remains of Vataos behind. Worse yet, Zov has stolen the Scepter of Fahir! Chase after him!\"\n\"That thieving rat is gone. Perhaps Peth knows where he might have scurried off to?\""}
