{"id": "3191", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3191", "title": "Cursed", "text": "Cursed is an ability from &lt;a href=\"Unique%20monsters\"&gt;Unique monsters&lt;/a&gt;. Players hit by such monsters have a 50% chance of being cursed with &lt;a href=\"Amplify%20Damage\"&gt;Amplify Damage&lt;/a&gt;, identical to its &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; counterpart. Taking any damage from such monsters can inflict the curse, including from the &lt;a href=\"Charged%20Bolt%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Charged Bolts&lt;/a&gt; released by &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Enchanted\"&gt;Lightning Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; monsters, the &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Nova%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Frost Nova&lt;/a&gt; released by &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Enchanted\"&gt;Cold Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; monsters, and the &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Fire\"&gt;Holy Fire&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Holy%20Freeze\"&gt;Freeze&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Holy%20Shock\"&gt;Shock&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Aura%20Enchanted\"&gt;Aura Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; monsters.\nWhen the curse takes effect on a player or a player's &lt;a href=\"Hirelings\"&gt;Hireling&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Pet\"&gt;summoned pets&lt;/a&gt;, the player, Hireling, and pets are all cursed if they are close enough to the monster, putting entire parties at risk of being cursed.\nCursed is a very deadly unique attribute, and Cursed uniques should always be approached with caution."}
{"id": "26729", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26729", "title": "Cursed Chest", "text": "A Cursed Chest is a special type of and appearing in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" where the chest is locked until the event is completed. All Cursed Chests look like large, dark metal chests with a red glimmer, and sometimes have a bubble around them while the event is being completed. When clicked, these chests start the corresponding event instead of opening.\nCursed Chest events require killing a number of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s or a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; as fast as possible, after which the Cursed Chest turns into one or two &lt;a href=\"Radiant%20Chest\"&gt;Radiant Chest&lt;/a&gt;s that can be looted. Two categories of Cursed Chest are found throughout the game world: minor ones with easier challenges that cause the chest to disappear if failed, and major ones with harder challenges which award a bonus chest if successful, and can be assigned as &lt;a href=\"bounties\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt;. A few special Cursed Chest types are limited to zones \"only\" accessible through bounties, but are otherwise similar to major chests. A very few may appear as part of other specific events.\nCursed Chests are never found in &lt;a href=\"Nephalem%20Rift\"&gt;Nephalem Rift&lt;/a&gt;s of either kind, nor other zones \"outside the main world\" such as &lt;a href=\"Follower\"&gt;Follower&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; zones (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Lair%20of%20the%20Prophet\"&gt;Lair of the Prophet&lt;/a&gt;) or special event zones like &lt;a href=\"Vision%20of%20Enmity\"&gt;Visions of Enmity&lt;/a&gt;.\nTypes of Cursed Chest.\nThe first two Cursed Chests types are most common: every game is very likely to contain quite a few Cursed Chests distributed throughout each &lt;a href=\"Act\"&gt;Act&lt;/a&gt;, including some in &lt;a href=\"Campaign%20Mode\"&gt;Campaign Mode&lt;/a&gt;. However, any specific Cursed Chest may or may not appear in any given game, and its exact location is somewhat randomized, like with other s. The remaining types of Cursed Chest are much less common, and some may only be found in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt;.\nMinor Cursed Chests.\nThese Cursed Chest events are found in many game zones and require killing a relatively small number of monsters as fast as possible. A highly geared character may be able to do this in a few seconds even at maximum difficulty. This simply cleanses and unlocks the &lt;a href=\"Radiant%20Chest\"&gt;Radiant Chest&lt;/a&gt;, while failure causes the chest to disappear. There are three variations:\nIn all cases, the monsters appear as soon as the chest is clicked, in the area surrounding it and the player.\nThese chests are not marked on the minimap until the player clicks on the chest, and are never selected as bounties. They follow the name format of \"Cursed Chest of the [monster description]\", such as the \"Cursed Chest of the Khazra\" or the more poetic \"Cursed Chest of the Hidden\".\nMajor Cursed Chests.\nThis category of Cursed Chest event also appears in many game zones, and requires killing a large number of normal monsters, spawning repeatedly en masse within a medium time window. A higher amount of damage output is required to accomplish the objective compared to minor chests, and positioning and spawning patterns can make it difficult to kill all monsters quickly. Success within the time limit grants a bonus &lt;a href=\"Radiant%20Chest\"&gt;Radiant Chest&lt;/a&gt;; failure still allows the single cleansed Radiant Chest to be opened once the remaining monsters are cleared. There are two subtypes:\nMajor Cursed Chests are the most common ones that can be assigned as &lt;a href=\"bounties\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt;. They share their bounty category with other s, so none may appear on some bounty maps, while there may be multiple on others. The bounty for a chest is completed once the event is done, regardless of whether the bonus chest was earned or not.\nThese types of chests are marked on the map from reasonably far away, even if not available as a bounty. They have the name format \"The Cursed [location]\", like \"The Cursed Shallows\" or \"The Cursed Mill\". These names show up on the &lt;a href=\"Act\"&gt;Act&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"map\"&gt;map&lt;/a&gt; when offered as a bounty.\nBounty Zone Cursed Chests.\nThese Cursed Chests are similar to the previous category in requiring more work than minor chests, having a guaranteed &lt;a href=\"Radiant%20Chest\"&gt;Radiant Chest&lt;/a&gt; reward, and allowing a bonus chest. However, the chests only appear in \"bounty zones\", which are only accessible for one of four specific &lt;a href=\"bounties\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt;. Any of the bounties are possible in any &lt;a href=\"Act\"&gt;Act&lt;/a&gt;, but not guaranteed. Any game is reasonably likely to contain one of this kind of chest somewhere in the world.\nBounty Zone chests do not follow standardized spawning patterns - each event has its own objectives, enemies, and objects. The chests themselves have no \"Cursed\" names; the event and the bounty instead share one of four possible names:\nAll of these events award a bonus chest for completing the full objective in time.\nAppearance in other events.\nRarely, another , such as &lt;a href=\"Leap%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Leap of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, may feature a chest with the same look as regular Cursed Chests, which is similarly locked until the event is completed. These events do not follow the same standardized time limit or monster spawning structure as other Cursed Chests and aren't named the same way, so they aren't categorized as Cursed Chest events on this wiki.\nCursed Shrines removed from the game.\nMost if not all Cursed Chest events with the \"five wave\" format were formerly &lt;a href=\"Shrines%20%28Diablo%20III%29%23Cursed%20Shrines\"&gt;Cursed Shrines&lt;/a&gt;, as were a number of the minor chests. This type of shrine was removed and replaced with chest versions, possibly around &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; 10. The Shrines awarded the bonus chests the same way as Cursed Chests did, but the base reward was a cleansed shrine rather than a chest.\nThe shrines were formerly covered by the achievements below, but upon being replaced, the achievements were updated as well to refer to the corresponding chest.\nAchievements and Conquests.\nCursed Chests are the subject of one \"Cursebreaker\" &lt;a href=\"achievement\"&gt;achievement&lt;/a&gt; per &lt;a href=\"act\"&gt;act&lt;/a&gt;. These require the player to complete all major Cursed Chest events in the act, but does not require any minor ones. They are named:\nIn some &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt;s, a &lt;a href=\"Conquest\"&gt;Conquest&lt;/a&gt; may be available to complete, requiring the player to kill at least 350 monsters in a single Cursed Chest event on &lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment X&lt;/a&gt; difficulty or higher. This can only be completed with a major chest found in the world. &lt;a href=\"The%20Cursed%20Peat\"&gt;The Cursed Peat&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Cursed%20Bellows\"&gt;The Cursed Bellows&lt;/a&gt; are known as the easiest Cursed Chests with which to achieve these high kill counts. The Conquest names are:\nThese Conquests were available during Seasons 6, 8, 12, 13, 16, 18, 20, 21, 24, 25, 28, and 30."}
