{"id": "41562", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41562", "title": "Cursed Grove", "text": "The Cursed Grove is a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt; zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is located right next to the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Battlecamp\"&gt;Rogue Battlecamp&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Fallen\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt; have made a village of their own inside the grove within trees blackened by Andariel's foul magics.\nIn-game.\nThe Cursed Grove zone is a Dark Wood zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is passed through on the player's way to the Rogue Battlecamp, and is returned to in the \"&lt;a href=\"Gathering%20the%20Reagents\"&gt;Gathering the Reagents&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. This prompts the player to visit the Fallen village (not an actual zone), which will trigger an event with the &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Matriarch\"&gt;Fallen Matriarch&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "49459", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49459", "title": "Cursed Items", "text": " are a variant of &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary Items&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They were introduced in the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Falling%20Towers\"&gt;Age of Falling Towers&lt;/a&gt; update. They can provide extremely powerful bonuses to bolster a character build.\n are obtainable from completing PvP matches in the &lt;a href=\"Accursed%20Towers\"&gt;Accursed Towers&lt;/a&gt; gameplay mode, and can also be dropped by enemies while collecting &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Shard\"&gt;Cursed Shard&lt;/a&gt;s from a PvE match. All Legendary Items that drop anywhere in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; also have a chance of being a Cursed Item.\n come with a positive property attached to them. The property will not activate unless the owner has at least one other Cursed Item equipped that shares the same property. Properties activate only when enemies are present, and will grow in power as the player equips multiple Cursed Items with the same property, with increases occurring at 4 and 6 items.\nHistory.\nOriginally, Cursed Items had negative properties attached to them. These could be one of the following:\nThe negative properties would only activate while the item's positive property was also active. Multiple instances of the same active negative property would stack. The &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt; update removed the negative properties, allowing the positive properties to be used without penalty."}
{"id": "33404", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33404", "title": "Cursed Matriarch", "text": "Cursed Matriarch\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Scouring%20Lobber\"&gt;Scouring Lobber&lt;/a&gt; found in any special zone accessed from the &lt;a href=\"portal\"&gt;portal&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". She only spawns for &lt;a href=\"A%20Plague%20of%20Burrowers\"&gt;A Plague of Burrowers&lt;/a&gt; event (one 6 Burrowers are killed, regardless of timing), and must be killed to finish it.\nIn combat, she has Illusionist and Frozen Pulse affixes."}
