{"id": "41166", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41166", "title": "Cycle of Strife", "text": "The Cycle of Strife is the never-ending battle between the &lt;a href=\"Immortals\"&gt;Immortals&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shadows\"&gt;Shadows&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe seeds of the Cycle of Strife lie with the formation of both groups. Per the orders of &lt;a href=\"Daedessa\"&gt;Daedessa&lt;/a&gt;, the Immortals were formed to guard &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; against &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic threats, while the Shadows were formed to constantly test the Immortals. It was agreed that if the Shadows ever defeated the Immortals, they would become Immortals themselves. This came to pass, with &lt;a href=\"Akeba\"&gt;Akeba&lt;/a&gt; becoming the next Immortal. However, not willing to rest on her laurels, she founded the Cycle of Strife, which has continued ever since, with the &lt;a href=\"Rite%20of%20Exile\"&gt;Rite of Exile&lt;/a&gt; reguarly being conducted, and beyond that, the &lt;a href=\"Challenge%20of%20the%20Immortal\"&gt;Challenge of the Immortal&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Cycle of Strife had been on for over a thousand years by the year &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, though was escalating by this point.\nGameplay.\nThe Cycle of Strife is a game mechanic of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is based on clans competing with one another. Each clan has the ability to become a \"dark clan\", whose members are &lt;a href=\"Shadows\"&gt;Shadows&lt;/a&gt;. If a Dark Clan defeats the Immortals in the &lt;a href=\"Rite%20of%20Exile\"&gt;Rite of Exile&lt;/a&gt;, the current Cycle ends, and a new Cycle begins. At that time, everything connected to the current Cycle resets. This includes all ranks, Eternal Crown levels, &lt;a href=\"Path%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Path of Blood&lt;/a&gt; progress, and so on. Additionally, when a Cycle ends, participating heroes earn &lt;a href=\"Deeds%20of%20Valor\"&gt;Deeds of Valor&lt;/a&gt;, special titles connected to their performance that Cycle. The former Immortal and their lieutenants will be engraved on the &lt;a href=\"Wall%20of%20Honor\"&gt;Wall of Honor&lt;/a&gt;, as a permanent place of remembrance to reflect on that group\u2019s reign.\nIf the Immortals successfully defeat the Shadows, the Cycle continues as normal.\nSchedule.\nStarting with the first week of the Immortal reign, the events of the Cycle follow a set schedule:\nRewards.\nThe reward for a blessed reign is a Blessed Reign Chest that contains 2 random &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;Set Items&lt;/a&gt;, 3 random &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary Items&lt;/a&gt; and 3 &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Crest\"&gt;Legendary Crest&lt;/a&gt;s. Furthermore, special cosmetics can be unlocked by accumulating 4 and 6 Blessed Reigns on a character.\nCycle's End.\nWhen the Immortal reign ends, the Cycle's End or Cycle's Turn is started. For the next week, a login reward can be claimed:\nFurthermore the &lt;a href=\"Cycle%27s%20Turn%20Chest\"&gt;Cycle's Turn Chest&lt;/a&gt; can be purchased from the &lt;a href=\"Hilts\"&gt;Hilts&lt;/a&gt; Trader.\nServer Merge.\nDuring a &lt;a href=\"server%20merge\"&gt;server merge&lt;/a&gt;, the alliance with the highest dominance is chosen to be the new Immortals. All other clans who were Immortals are reverted to &lt;a href=\"Adventurers\"&gt;Adventurers&lt;/a&gt;. The Cycle of Strife counter is set to the length of the reign of the Immortal alliance that was chosen to be the Immortals on the merged server.\nIf there was a reign change on the last Sunday before the merge, the Cycle's Turn daily rewards and the &lt;a href=\"Cycle%27s%20Turn%20Chest\"&gt;Cycle's Turn Chest&lt;/a&gt; option from the &lt;a href=\"Hilts\"&gt;Hilts&lt;/a&gt; vendor are cancelled before their regular end date.\n&lt;a href=\"Deeds%20of%20Valor\"&gt;Deeds of Valor&lt;/a&gt; scores are set to the maximum for all players as part of the merge.\nDevelopment.\nThe Cycle of Strife initially functioned differently. There would only ever be one group of Immortals on a server, with up to 500 members. There was no limit as to how many Shadows could be active, and they would all be vying to displace the current group of Immortals. The Cycle was expected to reset each month.\nPlayers could originally form &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Houses\"&gt;Dark Houses&lt;/a&gt;. This was replaced by the \"dark clan\" system.\nThe 7-week cycle with a fixed schedule was introduced in the September 21 2023 update.\nWhen the fixed cycle was introduced, Blessed Reign was earned by winning the Challenge of the Immortal on week 7, and the number of matches needed to win the Rite of Exile on week 6 was 3 for the Shadows (the outcome of the Rite on week 7 didn't affect the result of the event). In the update, Blessed Reign was changed to be earned by winning the Rite of Exile on week 7, and the number of matches the Shadows need to win was changed to 4 on weeks 6 and 7."}
{"id": "52479", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52479", "title": "Cyclone's Call", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; off hand &lt;a href=\"edge\"&gt;edge&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". When equipped, it enables the player to use a variant of &lt;a href=\"Crosswinds\"&gt;Crosswinds&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "2541", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2541", "title": "Cyclone Armor", "text": "Cyclone Armor is a &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"This skill allows the Druid to sheath himself in a swirling mass of charged particles that absorbs damage from fire-, cold-, and lightning-based attacks. \"\nIn-game.\nCyclone is a very useful skill for &lt;a href=\"Windy%20Druid\"&gt;Wind Druids&lt;/a&gt;, but not really for any other Druid build. It could be described as the elemental, windy version of ; it stays on your Druid until it absorbs a certain amount of &lt;a href=\"elemental%20damage\"&gt;elemental damage&lt;/a&gt;, or you leave the game. Unlike its &lt;a href=\"physical\"&gt;physical&lt;/a&gt; damage cousin, however, the synergies it receives are \"not\" flat additions, but rather percentage additions. It has its maximum effectiveness when its maxed with synergies, which is why it is best for Wind Druids who utilize it along with the other wind skills.\nAs tempting as investing in this skill can be for gearing purposes, it cannot serve as a complete substitute for equipment with &lt;a href=\"resistances\"&gt;resistances&lt;/a&gt;, although it can work together with those to provide the Druid with a second degree of elemental protection. &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; damage is absorbed, but &lt;a href=\"Freeze\"&gt;Freeze&lt;/a&gt; is not prevented.\nIts animation is of three white streaks circling the &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;. When a third (33%) of the total possible amount of damage absorbed is absorbed, one of the three streaks disappears. The second streak also disappears when 66% damage is absorbed, and the third streak disappears when 100% of the elemental damage is absorbed.\n&lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt; has a similar shield circling around him."}
{"id": "39070", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39070", "title": "Cyclone Armor (Diablo IV)", "text": "Cyclone Armor\u00a0is a Defensive Storm skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", loosely based on the &lt;a href=\"Cyclone%20Armor\"&gt;classic spell&lt;/a&gt; of the same name, but completely passive instead of semi-active.\nIn-game.\nWhile the damage reduction only applies to the ranged attackers, melee attacking enemies will also have a chance to be pushed away from the Druid. However, this effect has a &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt; for each particular foe, and some attacks (mostly those that deliver &lt;a href=\"damage%20over%20time\"&gt;damage over time&lt;/a&gt;) have a much lower chance to trigger it.\nSince Cyclone Armor deals no damage, it will not benefit from most talents and effects."}
{"id": "24635", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24635", "title": "Cyclone Strike", "text": "Cyclone Strike is a Focus &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nIn-game.\nWhen used, forcibly pulls enemies towards the Monk's location, followed by a 12 yard-radius blast that deals &lt;a href=\"Holy\"&gt;Holy&lt;/a&gt; damage with a very brief delay. Cannot pull enemies immune to &lt;a href=\"Knockback\"&gt;Knockback&lt;/a&gt;. Normally, all enemies that were pulled will suffer a hit from the blast."}
{"id": "43856", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43856", "title": "Cyclone Strike (Diablo Immortal)", "text": "Cyclone Strike is a skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "5967", "revid": "51979909", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5967", "title": "Cydaea", "text": "Cydaea, the Maiden of Lust was a powerful &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;, and a favorite &lt;a href=\"Sin%20Lieutenants\"&gt;lieutenant&lt;/a&gt; and concubine of Azmodan. \nBiography.\nCydaea was a consort of the Lord of Sin himself and one of his dreaded sin lieutenants. She also held dominion over a flock of &lt;a href=\"Succubi\"&gt;Succubi&lt;/a&gt;, calling them her &lt;a href=\"Daughters%20of%20Pain\"&gt;\"daughters\"&lt;/a&gt;. When Azmodan launched his &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;assault&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt;, Cydaea remained behind. However, when &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; thwarted the demonic incursion, Azmodan called upon his consort to defend the vile &lt;a href=\"Sin%20Heart\"&gt;Sin Heart&lt;/a&gt;s that powered his &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Sin\"&gt;legions&lt;/a&gt; from within &lt;a href=\"Arreat%20Crater\"&gt;Arreat Crater&lt;/a&gt;. However, like many other minions of Sin, Cydaea proved unable to stop The Nephalem. She was slain in the depths of Arreat Crater.\nIn-game.\nCydaea appears as a minor boss in the &lt;a href=\"Tower%20of%20the%20Cursed\"&gt;Tower of the Cursed&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", appearing when the Nephalem destroys the &lt;a href=\"Siegebreaker%20Assault%20Beast\"&gt;Siegebreaker Assault Beast&lt;/a&gt; and proceeds to make progress towards the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Heart of Sin&lt;/a&gt;. Cydaea will taunt the heroes seductively during their journey through the crater, dangling from a string of silk. Players will also encounter mind-controlled guards of &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt; who will say that Cydaea lured them with false promises and was preparing them to be sacrificed.\nThe player fights her twice, both times when a Sin Heart is within the heroes' reach. Both battles take place at a C-shaped arena, starting as soon as player approaches the Heart. The first battle is more like a gear-check, as she retreats immediately after receiving 50% damage, leaving the matter to her daughters and ghoul thralls.\nThe second and final battle at the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Cursed\"&gt;Heart of the Cursed&lt;/a&gt; is more complicated. Cydaea is the fastest boss in game, and often runs away from the player, forcing them to fight her &lt;a href=\"Spider\"&gt;spiderlings&lt;/a&gt; instead. She uses the following abilities:\nOn &lt;a href=\"Torment%20difficulty\"&gt;Torment difficulty&lt;/a&gt;, she has a semi-hard 4 minute enrage timer. Once it expires, she loses a cooldown of her Spiderling Pit and Net Toss abilities, overwhelming the players with the endless swarm of minions if not killed quickly.\u00a0As her own damage does not grow, however, she can still be defeated even on adequate difficulty.\nNote: Due to mechanics of her fight, it is actually the easiest boss in game for builds that rely on gaining power from killing blows (&lt;a href=\"Archon\"&gt;Archon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Grave%20Injustice\"&gt;Grave Injustice&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dominance\"&gt;Dominance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rampage\"&gt;Rampage&lt;/a&gt; etc.).\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Binder\"&gt;The Binder&lt;/a&gt; is the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Rift%20Guardian\"&gt;Rift Guardian&lt;/a&gt; variant of Cydaea."}
{"id": "24398", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24398", "title": "Cynthia Hall", "text": "Cynthia Hall is a quality assurance analyst at &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Entertainment\"&gt;Blizzard Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;. She has cosplayed for both the \"&lt;a href=\"Warcraft\"&gt;Warcraft&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Series\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\" series, specifically as the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Hunter\"&gt;Demon Hunter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Malthael\"&gt;Malthael&lt;/a&gt; in the case of the latter. These costumes are available on her website."}
