{"id": "50726", "revid": "44564686", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50726", "title": "Cyrangar Depths", "text": "The , also called Depths of Cyrangar, is the dark underbelly of &lt;a href=\"Castle%20Cyrangar\"&gt;Castle Cyrangar&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nCyrangar's Depths is filled with &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; half-rotted with age, and &lt;a href=\"Bound%20Guardian\"&gt;restless spirits&lt;/a&gt; bound to the castle for all eternity.\nIn-game.\n is the site of Purge the Depths gameplay. It has a central hall which contains the Accursed Altar. The hall is connected to three wings whos interior are randomized. There's a chance to come across special rooms (Bunkroom, Library, Scroll Room, Well etc) whose doors are closed. These rooms have been infested with evil and filled with darkness. The player has to complete a specific task to dispel the darkness. Once finished the rooms will contain at least one Timeworn Chest."}
{"id": "50493", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50493", "title": "Cyrangar Outer Hall", "text": ", also known as Cyrangar's Main Hall is the the initial zone of &lt;a href=\"Castle%20Cyrangar\"&gt;Castle Cyrangar&lt;/a&gt;. After \"&lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Expedition\"&gt;Ruined Expedition&lt;/a&gt;\", it is made into a camp for the &lt;a href=\"Warband\"&gt;Warband&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\n is the foyer of Castle Cyrangar. The &lt;a href=\"Ancestral%20Tableu\"&gt;Ancestral Tableu&lt;/a&gt; resides in the center of the hall. Two wings are connected to the hall, leading to a total of eight rooms. At the end of the hall is a set of doors that lead to &lt;a href=\"Cyrangar%20Depths\"&gt;the underbelly&lt;/a&gt; of the castle.\nHistory.\nAround &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231271\"&gt;1271&lt;/a&gt;, a warband made an expedition to Castle Cyrangar. At the outer hall of the castle, they encountered a green haze, which drove them to madness, then death. &lt;a href=\"Ferdinan\"&gt;One&lt;/a&gt; managed to make it back to &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, and deliver the news to &lt;a href=\"Valstus\"&gt;his friend&lt;/a&gt; before dying. Valstus \u2014the friend, together with an adventurer, returned to the castle and were able to destroy the source of the haze, and kill many &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; roaming the castle.\nThe adventurer later returned with a warband, and by then Valstus had cleared the outer hall of undead, and prepared a camp for the warband at the bailey.\nIn-game.\n is a zone of Castle Cyrangar featured in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;.\" It is the initial area of the castle. This zone also includes the bailey at the the castle's entrance, and two wings connected to the opposite ends of the hall.\nThe bailey is the warband camp, which includes the warband banner, a bonfire where photos of the warband can be taken, an armory, a &lt;a href=\"blacksmith\"&gt;blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; and an &lt;a href=\"identifier\"&gt;identifier&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe wings contain rooms which provides unique bonuses to its occupant, which is decided by the warband leader."}
