{"id": "41151", "revid": "24618333", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41151", "title": "Daedessa", "text": "Daedessa the Builder was a &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nLong before the rise of &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;ity, Daedessa constructed the city of &lt;a href=\"Corvus\"&gt;Corvus&lt;/a&gt;. One of her companions, &lt;a href=\"Lidar\"&gt;Lidar&lt;/a&gt;, infused the city with a form of &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; that would ward off trespassing &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. \nDaedessa wanted to protect &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; from demonic invasion, but while powerful, she wasn't a fighter. She was, however, a master crafter, and she created a powerful artifact called the &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Crown\"&gt;Eternal Crown&lt;/a&gt;. In Corvus, she gave it to her son, &lt;a href=\"Kion\"&gt;Kion&lt;/a&gt;, and charged him with forming a group whose sole purpose would be the protection of Sanctuary from the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt;. The group was called the &lt;a href=\"Immortals\"&gt;Immortals&lt;/a&gt;, and she worked the resplendent armor of the greatest of their number.\nHowever, Daedessa knew that power could lead to complacency and corruption for even the best intentioned individuals, so to this end, entrusted her daughter, &lt;a href=\"Akeba\"&gt;Akeba&lt;/a&gt;, with a secret burden; to ensure that the Immortals would never waver or falter, that they were always capable of defending Sanctuary, to establish a group of her own specifically for such purpose, the Shadows. \nAt some point, Daedessa disappeared.\nIn-game.\nDaedessa has a presence in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Players can earn the \"Blessing of Daedessa\" by completing &lt;a href=\"Kion%27s%20Ordeal\"&gt;Kion's Ordeal&lt;/a&gt;, which increases rewards for Elder Rift runs.\nHer face appears on &lt;a href=\"crests\"&gt;crests&lt;/a&gt;."}
