{"id": "26280", "revid": "51381002", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26280", "title": "Daibo", "text": "Daibo are a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Classes\"&gt;class-specific&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0type of &lt;a href=\"staves\"&gt;staves&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are significantly faster than most other two-handed weapons, and in addition to stats that all weapons can roll, can also have increased damage of Monk skills, &lt;a href=\"Spirit\"&gt;Spirit&lt;/a&gt; regeneration, &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; per Spirit spent and maximum Spirit. Daibo may appear both bladed and blunt, but always double-ended, a weighted or sharp head on each end of the pole.\nDaibo may be &lt;a href=\"transmog\"&gt;transmog&lt;/a&gt;rified into Staves, &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20Axes\"&gt;Two-Handed Axes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20Maces\"&gt;Two-Handed Maces&lt;/a&gt;, but only Monks can do the other way."}
