{"id": "41198", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41198", "title": "Damned Cultist", "text": "Damned Cultists are a type of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are members of the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Cult of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nIt is rare to come of age amidst the horrors of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; without a few grievances. Despite its grisly course, &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Damnation's&lt;/a&gt; message is seductive to many more people than the \"civilized\" folks of &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt; might expect. It preordains punishments for the defiant \u2014 and, for the supplicant, the opportunity to swing the executioner's axe at last.\nIn-game.\nThey appear in the game's starting area (around &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt;), in the northern part of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt;, and in &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;. They can summon &lt;a href=\"Infested%20Villager\"&gt;Infested Villager&lt;/a&gt;s.\nDamned Cultists come in two models; the males are usually armed with short spears attack at melee or summon either &lt;a href=\"Engorged%20Leech\"&gt;Engorged Leech&lt;/a&gt;es or &lt;a href=\"Hellion\"&gt;Hellion&lt;/a&gt;s. When unarmed, they can attack using bolts of &lt;a href=\"blood%20magic\"&gt;blood magic&lt;/a&gt; from their deformed hands.\nThe females are ranged fighters using blood magic."}
{"id": "45723", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45723", "title": "Damned Summoner", "text": "The is one of the classes of cultists in the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Cult of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;. They are superior to &lt;a href=\"Damned%20Cultist\"&gt;Damned Cultist&lt;/a&gt;s in hierarchy.\nIn-game.\nDamned Summoners can shoot &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt;balls with their normal hands, and use their mutated hands for melee swipes. They can also partially summon &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s that throw fireballs at the player. They are mainly found in the &lt;a href=\"Refuge%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Refuge of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;."}
