{"id": "16464", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16464", "title": "Damos", "text": "Damos was the leader of the band of &lt;a href=\"Morlu\"&gt;Morlu&lt;/a&gt; in service of the &lt;a href=\"Primus\"&gt;Primus&lt;/a&gt;. He was dispatched to capture &lt;a href=\"Uldyssian\"&gt;Uldyssian&lt;/a&gt; along with &lt;a href=\"High%20Priest\"&gt;High Priest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Malic\"&gt;Malic&lt;/a&gt; and five of his best men. \nDamos was described as being a particularly large and brutish Morlu warrior. In life, Damos had been a dark and unspeakably evil human. A veteran of countless battles, Damos was resurrected a great number of times by the dark power of the &lt;a href=\"Kiss%20of%20Mephisto\"&gt;Kiss of Mephisto&lt;/a&gt; - in fact so many times that not even the power of the artifact could restore him completely. Of his nose not much was left save two holes. His lower jaw was so large it was speculated to have been of a different creature, possibly a bear. His eyes - nothing more but two dark pits - were misaligned. Still Damos skill and ruthlessness was unmatched and he served his master unquestioned. \nDuring the raid on &lt;a href=\"Ethon\"&gt;Ethon's&lt;/a&gt; estate, Damos disguised himself as the merchant's son, &lt;a href=\"Cedric\"&gt;Cedric&lt;/a&gt;. Damos ultimately met his - permanent - demise at the hands of &lt;a href=\"Mendeln\"&gt;Mendeln&lt;/a&gt;, who put his undead form to rest by means of an ancient spell."}
{"id": "40931", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40931", "title": "Damotrius", "text": "Damotrius was a soldier of &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, stationed at &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;siege&lt;/a&gt; of the fortress. He survived the assault, as well as &lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt;'s betrayal, the latter of which sent him into despair like many of those who'd survived. However, his spirits were buoyed by &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Haile\"&gt;Captain Haile&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "17409", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17409", "title": "Damp Cellar", "text": "A Damp Cellar\u00a0is a very small dungeon in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It can appear under one of the buildings along the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Old%20Tristram%20Road\"&gt;Old Tristram Road&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0and must be explored to complete the achievement\u00a0&lt;a href=\"No%20Stone%20Unturned\"&gt;No Stone Unturned&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0The area sometimes houses &lt;a href=\"The%20Cursed%20Cellar\"&gt;The Cursed Cellar&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Chest\"&gt;Cursed Chest&lt;/a&gt; event in which the &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; zombie &lt;a href=\"Farnham\"&gt;Farnham&lt;/a&gt; appears.\nIf there is no cursed chest, there will instead be a dead &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt; militiaman or a &lt;a href=\"Chests%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;chest&lt;/a&gt; in the middle of the square main room. If the player interacts with it, a number of &lt;a href=\"Risen\"&gt;Risen&lt;/a&gt; will slowly emerge from the ground all around the dungeon."}
