{"id": "37561", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37561", "title": "Daring Swing", "text": " is a skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It allows the Demon Hunter to swing across the battlefield. The Demon Hunter will fire &lt;a href=\"arrows\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"monsters\"&gt;monsters&lt;/a&gt; (and players, in PvP) in a straight line while swinging. The swing speed is determined not by movement speed, but by attack speed.\nFor a brief time, the skill allowed players to swing through walls and other barriers; this was rolled back because it allowed unintended behavior, letting players swing over barriers in set dungeons before completing necessary objectives. Developers intend to bring this feature back in a future patch."}
