{"id": "46793", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46793", "title": "Dark Cardinal Maldul", "text": "Dark Cardinal Maldul is a &lt;a href=\"Stronghold%20Bosses\"&gt;Stronghold Boss&lt;/a&gt; encountered in &lt;a href=\"Altar%20of%20Ruin\"&gt;Altar of Ruin&lt;/a&gt;. He is a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;super unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Summoner%20%28Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Dark Summoner&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nDark Cardinal Maldul is a final &lt;a href=\"Bosses\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Altar%20of%20Ruin\"&gt;Altar of Ruin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt;. He is fought in two phases.\nIn the first phase, he will summon &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20%28Diablo%20IV%29\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt;, including an elite &lt;a href=\"The%20Annihilator\"&gt;The Annihilator&lt;/a&gt;. After killing all Fallen, he will summon a unique &lt;a href=\"Balrog\"&gt;Balrog&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"The%20Unholy\"&gt;The Unholy&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter killing The Unholy, Maldul will fight the player himself. He will throw projectiles, summon &lt;a href=\"Khazra\"&gt;Khazra&lt;/a&gt; and create damaging circles."}
