{"id": "21002", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21002", "title": "Gazing Demise", "text": "Gazing Demise is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mojo\"&gt;Mojo&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 8 to drop.\nThis is one of the few items with 5 primary affixes. As a free 7th affix as of Patch 2.4.2, it gained the ability to empower &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Barrage\"&gt;Spirit Barrage&lt;/a&gt;. Gazing Demise not only adds the Phantasm rune summoning the specters in addition to normal fire, but it also multiplicatively increases damage done by the skill. \nAs of Patch 2.6.8, it also doubles the duration of Phantasms and the &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt; of Manitou.\nPatch 2.7.0 removed the per Phantasm Spectres damage bonus that was originally added in Patch 2.4.2."}
{"id": "3049", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3049", "title": "Gea Kul", "text": "Gea Kul is a &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Kehjistan\"&gt;Kehjistan&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nGea Kul is a port town located within Kehjistan, located north of &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;, across a river. It has a city square. It is known for its lawless streets.\nHistory.\nGea Kul existed by the late 11th century. In this period, it had a fighting pit overseen by &lt;a href=\"Morrick\"&gt;Morrick&lt;/a&gt;. In &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;1264&lt;/a&gt;, the town acted as a crossroads for travelers, but by &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, the town was a \"wasteland,\" and had suffered from urban sprawl, consisting of shoddy buildings and confusing intersections.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Malphas\"&gt;Malphas&lt;/a&gt; began possessing Gea Kul townsfolk.\nIn-game.\nGea Kul appears as a town in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It is the main hub of Kehjistan (in a game sense), though plays no major role in the game's primary questline. "}
{"id": "39419", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39419", "title": "Gears of Dreadlands", "text": "Gears of Dreadlands is a Class &lt;a href=\"Set\"&gt;Set&lt;/a&gt; for s added in patch 2.6.9 in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", obtainable at level 70. It can only drop on &lt;a href=\"Torment\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; difficulty.\nAll set pieces are restricted to Demon Hunters. Even\u00a0&lt;a href=\"transmogrification\"&gt;transmogrification&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of these items is only available to Demon Hunters.\nNOTE: There is no Set Dungeon for this set.\nPieces.\nThe set consists of six pieces, all six of which are required to complete it, and all six are Demon Hunter-restricted.\nSet Bonus:\nFor the first bonus, Momentum applies when casting the ability (but only once per cast), and is a singular buff that affects all Primary skills at once.\nHowever, there is a limit on how many Primary skill projectiles this effect can benefit at a time; if too many of them are out, new ones will not grant Momentum stacks until the old ones despawn. This is not often an issue with most skills, but with &lt;a href=\"Hungering%20Arrow\"&gt;Hungering Arrow&lt;/a&gt; (which can pierce multiple times) this may force the character to take a pause.\nFor the second bonus, it is able to proc some bonuses and other powers with the Strafe-fired Primary skills, but not all of them.\nEffects that \"do\" trigger:\nEffects that \"do\" NOT trigger:\nMomentum also weakens over time, therefore every once in a while the Demon Hunter will have to cast their Primary skill manually.\nThe per second of Momentum speed/damage bonus is different from the original 'per stack' one: it means +8% and +10% for each remaining second of Momentum, up to 20, that is, up to +160% speed and +200% damage. For convenience, the remaining duration is displayed as stacks on the buff itself.\nFor maximum effect, this set can be combined with &lt;a href=\"Odyssey%27s%20End\"&gt;Odyssey's End&lt;/a&gt; (with &lt;a href=\"Entangling%20Shot\"&gt;Entangling Shot&lt;/a&gt;) and &lt;a href=\"The%20Ninth%20Cirri%20Satchel\"&gt;The Ninth Cirri Satchel&lt;/a&gt; (with &lt;a href=\"Hungering%20Arrow\"&gt;Hungering Arrow&lt;/a&gt;), with some builds featuring both."}
