{"id": "21062", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21062", "title": "Genzaniku", "text": "The Genzaniku is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"axes\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 8 to drop.\nThe special affix summons a ghostly &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Overseer%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Fallen Overseer&lt;/a&gt; for 10 seconds. Attacks can trigger it even if they do not hit anything."}
{"id": "54512", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54512", "title": "Geoffrey Staalek", "text": "Geoffrey Staalek was the constable of &lt;a href=\"Staalbreak\"&gt;Staalbreak&lt;/a&gt;, the husband of &lt;a href=\"Marenna%20Staalek\"&gt;Marenna Staalek&lt;/a&gt;, and the father of &lt;a href=\"Jacob%20Staalek\"&gt;Jacob Staalek&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nEarly Life.\nAt some point in his life, Geoffrey had a son named &lt;a href=\"Jacob%20Staalek\"&gt;Jacob&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Marenna%20Staalek\"&gt;Marenna Staalek&lt;/a&gt;, a . Geoffrey taught Jacob how to use a sword and to not let emotion get the better of him in a fight.\nSplintered Souls.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; was shattered, Geoffrey and Marenna made &lt;a href=\"Outsiders%27%20Camp\"&gt;a camp for the refugees&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Southern%20Dreadlands\"&gt;Southern Dreadlands&lt;/a&gt;, which was led by Marenna, while Geoffrey and other volunteers plotted a revolt against the laird.\nThe Unmaking.\nGeoffrey was one of the defenders of Staalbreak fighting demons during &lt;a href=\"the%20Unmaking\"&gt;the Unmaking&lt;/a&gt;.\nSword of Justice.\nBlood is the Spark.\nSometime after the destruction of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Mount Arreat&lt;/a&gt;, Staalbreak was attacked by a force. The battle, which Jacob was a part of, ended in Staalbreak's favor. Geoffrey found Jacob beside &lt;a href=\"Ivan\"&gt;Ivan&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt;, and berated his son for following Ivan over the walls. Jacob mentioned past words from his father about his oath to protect the people.\nYears later, Geoffrey became infected with the &lt;a href=\"Rage%20Plague\"&gt;Rage Plague&lt;/a&gt; and became paranoid. He accused Marenna of betrayal and she was soon executed. After her execution, Geoffrey dueled Jacob, resulting Geoffrey's death and Jacob fleeing Staalbreak.\nLegacy.\nAfter Geoffrey's death, Jacob experienced visions of him and was later visited by his &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;spirit&lt;/a&gt; (or hallucinated it), who reassured him that he wasn't a murderer. However, the vision of Geoffrey transformed into his demeanor during his final moments, that of a madman."}
