{"id": "45391", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45391", "title": "Gergel's Familiarity", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"pants\"&gt;pants&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". When equipped, it enables the player to use a variant of &lt;a href=\"Mystic%20Strike\"&gt;Mystic Strike&lt;/a&gt;.\n bears cosmetic synergy with the Legendary items; &lt;a href=\"Resurgency\"&gt;Resurgency&lt;/a&gt; (head) &lt;a href=\"Fate%20Alight\"&gt;Fate Alight&lt;/a&gt; (shoulders), &lt;a href=\"Ordered%20Obsidian\"&gt;Ordered Obsidian&lt;/a&gt; (chest), &lt;a href=\"Arc%20of%20the%20Ascendants\"&gt;Arc of the Ascendants&lt;/a&gt; (main hand), and &lt;a href=\"Willbillow\"&gt;Willbillow&lt;/a&gt; (off hand). They are all available as drops from I and above."}
{"id": "6464", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6464", "title": "Gerke's Sanctuary", "text": "Gerke's Sanctuary is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Pavise\"&gt;Pavise&lt;/a&gt;, a type of &lt;a href=\"Shields\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; from \"\".\nA great defensive shield, Gerke's Sanctuary is a good option for physical fighters that prefer defensive bonuses to offense.\nGerke's Sanctuary has the highest chance to &lt;a href=\"block\"&gt;block&lt;/a&gt; out of all unique shields. Not only &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;s, but all &lt;a href=\"classes\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; can almost max out their block by using Gerke's Sanctuary. This and its high defense make Gerke's Sanctuary a sanctuary indeed.\nAdditionally, Gerke's Sanctuary gives a boost to all &lt;a href=\"Resistances\"&gt;Resistances&lt;/a&gt;. Due to the lowered resistances in and &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;difficulties&lt;/a&gt;, it is generally good for any shield to have this property.\nPerhaps as a secondary property, Gerke's Sanctuary also gives a bonus to &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; Replenish. Although no skill increases Life Replenish (unlike what &lt;a href=\"Warmth\"&gt;Warmth&lt;/a&gt; does for &lt;a href=\"Mana\"&gt;Mana&lt;/a&gt;), it can be raised to effective amounts when combined with items such as , &lt;a href=\"The%20Rising%20Sun\"&gt;The Rising Sun&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Skin%20of%20the%20Flayed%20One\"&gt;Skin of the Flayed One&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Verdungo%27s%20Hearty%20Cord\"&gt;Verdungo's Hearty Cord&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis shield also provides high integer &lt;a href=\"damage%20reduction\"&gt;damage reduction&lt;/a&gt; to both physical and magical attacks. This is great to prevent damage dealt through multiple frames, such as or poison clouds.\nGerke's Sanctuary does require a very high amount of &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield, making it problematic for those who would rather invest in other stats such as &lt;a href=\"Vitality\"&gt;Vitality&lt;/a&gt;.\nStats.\nDefense: 221-268\nRequired Level: 44\nRequired Strength: 133\nDurability: 172\nChance to Block:\nPaladin &lt;a href=\"Smite\"&gt;Smite&lt;/a&gt; Damage: 10 To 17"}
{"id": "48251", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48251", "title": "Gerlach", "text": "Gerlach was a resident of &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt; around the time the island was &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;attacked&lt;/a&gt; by the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nAfter the incident with the cult, Gerlach was desperate to leave the island. At a point, he discovered that some &lt;a href=\"Cultists\"&gt;Cultists&lt;/a&gt; were venerating a glowing red gem. Knowing that a gem like that would fetch a good price, he devised a plan with a friend to steal the gem \u2014 he would distract the Cultists, while &lt;a href=\"Franskie\"&gt;Franskie&lt;/a&gt; would steal the gem and send a signal after he succeeded.\nInstead of doing his part, Gerlach went to wait at a corner for Franskie's signal, which did not come. He employed the help of &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;an adventurer&lt;/a&gt; to help him steal the gem. After dispatching the nearby cultists, the duo noticed a dessicated &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt; near the gem, which turned out to be Franskie's. The adventure warned him that though the gem wasn't a &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; shard, it would likely be dangerous if Cultists were looking for it. Franskie didn't listen and went to grab the gem.\nUnfortunately, the gem had &lt;a href=\"Possessor\"&gt;a spirit&lt;/a&gt; within it, which tried to possess Gerlach. Luckily for him, his companion freed him and broke the gem.\nIn-game.\nGerlach is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He gives the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Good%20Host\"&gt;Good Host&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "21518", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21518", "title": "Gesture of Orpheus", "text": "Gesture of Orpheus is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Wands\"&gt;Wand&lt;/a&gt; for the in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 50 to drop.\nWhile it provides a significant &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt; reduction for &lt;a href=\"Slow%20Time\"&gt;Slow Time&lt;/a&gt; (the affix is not re-rollable), this wand is mostly valued for being the only weapon in game capable of increasing all 4 types of Wizard &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Damage\"&gt;Elemental Damage&lt;/a&gt; for skills, up to 20% at level 70.\nPrior to patch 2.2.0, it could only increase &lt;a href=\"Arcane\"&gt;Arcane&lt;/a&gt; skill damage, making it especially valuable to Arcane build users."}
