{"id": "41856", "revid": "51979909", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41856", "title": "Giant Vulture", "text": "Giant Vultures, also called Dire Vultures are carrion birds commonly found in the desserts and woodlands of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nSanctuary's vultures are a well-fed lot. Due to the preponderance of pestilent carrion in their diet, they are immune to most &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt;s. As they circle overhead, they drip plagued offal from feathers they have never once preened.\nIn-game.\ns are &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;animal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s featured in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be found in &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Windswept%20Sands\"&gt;Windswept Sands&lt;/a&gt;, and in &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Derelict%20Timberyard\"&gt;Derelict Timberyard&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "20496", "revid": "3459498", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20496", "title": "Gibbering", "text": ""}
{"id": "18829", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18829", "title": "Gibbering Gemstone", "text": "The Gibbering Gemstone is a miscellaneous &lt;a href=\"Craftable%20items\"&gt;crafting material&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;.\" It is used to construct the &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Herding\"&gt;Staff of Herding&lt;/a&gt;, which is necessary to access &lt;a href=\"Whimsyshire\"&gt;Whimsyshire&lt;/a&gt; and complete the &lt;a href=\"Altar%20of%20Rites\"&gt;Altar of Rites&lt;/a&gt; each &lt;a href=\"season\"&gt;season&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt has an &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; of 1 and requires a character level of 1. It is &lt;a href=\"Bind%20on%20Account\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt; as soon as it drops.\nAcquisition.\nThe Gemstone drops from &lt;a href=\"Chiltara\"&gt;Chiltara&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Lacuni%20Huntress\"&gt;Lacuni Huntress&lt;/a&gt; who sometimes spawns in Level 2 of the &lt;a href=\"Caverns%20of%20Frost\"&gt;Caverns of Frost&lt;/a&gt;. The Caverns are located under the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Slaughter\"&gt;Fields of Slaughter&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt;, most easily accessed via the &lt;a href=\"The%20Bridge%20of%20Korsikk\"&gt;The Bridge of Korsikk&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"waypoint\"&gt;waypoint&lt;/a&gt; just to the south. They are a guaranteed mutually exclusive shared spawn with the &lt;a href=\"Icefall%20Caves\"&gt;Icefall Caves&lt;/a&gt; - one or the other will always appear in a given game session, but not both.\nThe dungeon, the monster, and the item each have a chance not to appear, so repeated attempts to find the Gemstone are almost always needed. Gemstone drop rate from Chiltara has been estimated at around 5%. Chiltara herself was initially a fairly rare spawn, but &lt;a href=\"Patch%202.0.5%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Patch 2.0.5&lt;/a&gt; increased the rate to around 50%. The Caverns of Frost unfortunately seem to be somewhat less common than the Icefall Caves alternative.\nThe caves can spawn in any of several possible locations on the map. They share the same set of possible locations with the ballistae for the quest, even if the quest is completed, in which case the ballistae locations will just be empty. In Adventure Mode, the ballistae will always be present.\n&lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; is recommended to hunt for the gem - the waypoints are the same, there is no distraction from quests or NPCs, and the Act III &lt;a href=\"bounties\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt; often provide a clue as to which cave dungeon is available before actually visiting the zone. Specifically, if one is offered to kill Chiltara or clear the Caverns of Frost, then the zone is obviously present and worth clearing. Even better, map navigation arrows lead directly to the Caverns entrance in this case. On the other hand, if the task is to clear the Icefall Caves or complete &lt;a href=\"The%20Cursed%20Glacier\"&gt;The Cursed Glacier&lt;/a&gt; which occurs there, then the correct Caverns are not present, and the game can be restarted immediately. \nPlayers who do choose to search for the stone in &lt;a href=\"Campaign%20Mode\"&gt;Campaign Mode&lt;/a&gt; can select the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Machines%20of%20War\"&gt;Machines of War&lt;/a&gt;\" or later in Act III."}
