{"id": "43305", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43305", "title": "Gishtur", "text": "Gishtur, along with his twin brother &lt;a href=\"Beledwe\"&gt;Beledwe&lt;/a&gt;, were powerful &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, and members of the &lt;a href=\"Wrathborne\"&gt;Wrathborne&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nBeledwe and Gishtur were \"twin flames\", forged from the same inseparable, swirling chaos\" of the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt;. The pair gave each other form, and crafted every malefic weapon they could imagine. Their works are among some of the most formidable weapons to have graced the battlefield, operating the &lt;a href=\"Hellforge\"&gt;Hellforge&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Evils\"&gt;Great Evils&lt;/a&gt; or fusing &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s and flesh in their own &lt;a href=\"Fellsteel%20Foundry\"&gt;Fellsteel Foundry&lt;/a&gt;, reserving only the finest armaments for their own personal use. Gishtur favored battling his foes in close-quarters, sporting a massive, spiked sword and entering a frenzied whirlwind to close any gap. They were both known to incinerate opponents side-by-side.\nThe twins were detected by &lt;a href=\"Rayek\"&gt;Rayek&lt;/a&gt; in the year &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, and through the &lt;a href=\"Einfrinn%20Tree\"&gt;Einfrinn Tree&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; was dispatched to the Foundry. Both of the twins were slain.\nEve of Unmaking.\nC. &lt;a href=\"timeline%231273\"&gt;1273&lt;/a&gt;, Gishtur and his brother had resurrected in Hell. At the latter part of the year they\u2014along with &lt;a href=\"Vitaath\"&gt;Vitaath&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Gorgothra\"&gt;Gorgothra&lt;/a&gt;, led a &lt;a href=\"vanguard\"&gt;vanguard&lt;/a&gt; force to the &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Ravine\"&gt;Ashen Ravine&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nBeledwe and Gishtur are a double &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", and were the fourth &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; boss in the game. The player fights them inside the Felsteel Foundry. Gishtur attacks the player(s) via melee attacks. Finishing the fight awards players with &lt;a href=\"Twin%20Horns\"&gt;Twin Horns&lt;/a&gt;.\nOriginally defeating the pair was required to unlocking IV difficulty, but after the difficulty rework in the &lt;a href=\"Unending%20Storm\"&gt;Unending Storm&lt;/a&gt; update, this was scrapped. They can now be challenged on Normal difficulty.\nCombat.\nGishtur makes his entrance in the second phase of the battle, where he substitutes for Gishtur. He uses the following skills:"}
