{"id": "30737", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30737", "title": "Glowing Death", "text": "Glowing Death is a variant of the &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Wasp\"&gt;Sand Wasp&lt;/a&gt; encountered on &lt;a href=\"Greyhollow%20Island\"&gt;Greyhollow Island&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOriginally, they were supposed to be included in patch 2.3, and appear in the &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Ruins of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt; in , but were moved to patch 2.4 instead.\nIn-game.\nGlowing Death are much more aggressive than its desert counterpart, and while they have a spit attack, are more inclined to attack players directly. Their missiles deal &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; and fly \"much\" faster than normal Wasps'.\nHowever, unlike normal Wasps, they only spawn when a fragile nest (called Glowing Hive) is destroyed, in packs of 4 to 6. Avoiding the nest and not touching it (the Hive itself is completely harmless) is possible; however, as Hives are usually surrounded by other monsters, hitting them accidentally will instanly summon Glowing Deaths."}
