{"id": "48081", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48081", "title": "Gl\u00f3r-an-Fh\u00e1idha", "text": ", the Great Oak is a magnificent oak tree that stands at the heart of &lt;a href=\"T%C3%BAr%20D%C3%BAlra\"&gt;T\u00far D\u00falra&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\n is the most revered source of the &lt;a href=\"Druids\"&gt;Druids&lt;/a&gt;' guidance and teachings. It takes back to the time of &lt;a href=\"Vasily\"&gt;Vasily&lt;/a&gt;, who taught his kin under the Great Oak's branches. It is said that when he first taught, a raven perched in the tree to listen.\nUnder its branches, for centuries, the Druids have honied not only their powerful arsenal of natural &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and the martial skills they retained from their forefathers. The tree is watched over by the &lt;a href=\"Keepers\"&gt;Keepers&lt;/a&gt;; their wooden armor stands as a symbol of their connection with the tree, and their &lt;a href=\"staves\"&gt;staves&lt;/a&gt; are fashioned from its branches.\nRoots from the Great Oak growing at the seaward statue of Vasily will, on rare occasions, be found twisted back upon themselves, suffused with ferocious magic."}
