{"id": "31445", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31445", "title": "Goatman (Diablo I)", "text": "Goatmen (a.k.a. Goat Demons) are a type of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; encounter in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGameplay.\nMany Goatmen are found in the Catacombs area of the game. They are represented by the &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Clan\"&gt;Flesh Clan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Clan\"&gt;Stone Clan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Clan\"&gt;Fire Clan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Night%20Clan\"&gt;Night Clan&lt;/a&gt;, increasing in power in that sequence. These creatures are equipped with &lt;a href=\"Morning%20Star%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Morning Stars&lt;/a&gt;, and are separate from &lt;a href=\"Goatman%20Archer\"&gt;Goatman Archer&lt;/a&gt;s in game terms. "}
{"id": "31450", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31450", "title": "Goatman (Diablo II)", "text": "Goatmen appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", with a similar appearance to how they were portrayed in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\", though without archer variations or &lt;a href=\"super%20unique\"&gt;super unique&lt;/a&gt;s.\nIn-game.\nGoatmen often wield &lt;a href=\"bardiche\"&gt;bardiche&lt;/a&gt;s in battle. They are classified as &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, and hail from five different clans\u2014the &lt;a href=\"Moon%20Clan\"&gt;Moon Clan&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Night%20Clan\"&gt;Night Clan&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Clan\"&gt;Blood Clan&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Death%20Clan\"&gt;Death Clan&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Hell%20Clan\"&gt;Hell Clan&lt;/a&gt;, gaining in power in that order. They are found in , bar the Hell Clan, which is found in .\nThe Night Clan has a 15/20% chance to deal &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%29\"&gt;Lightning damage&lt;/a&gt; in and difficulties, while the Blood and Hell Clans have a 20/25%, 25/30% chance to deal &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage in said difficulties. \nDevelopment.\nBeta montype.txt file makes reference to Ice Clan, which is presumably the old name of Moon Clan, additionaly russian.txt has names of Wood Clan and Rock Clan (May be an old name of Death clan)."}
{"id": "40673", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40673", "title": "Goatman (Guest)", "text": "This is a page for &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; difficulty exclusive &lt;a href=\"Guest%20Monsters\"&gt;Guest&lt;/a&gt; variations of &lt;a href=\"Goatman%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Goatmen&lt;/a&gt;. \nAll Guest Goatmen are faster than normal &lt;a href=\"Goatman%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Hell Clan&lt;/a&gt; members and have varying resistances to everything. "}
{"id": "9475", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9475", "title": "Goatman Archer", "text": "Goatman Archers are a ranged enemy type encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nAlongside &lt;a href=\"Goatman%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Goatman Warriors&lt;/a&gt;, Archers can be found on many levels, ranging from the Cathedral to the Catacombs and Caves. They are classified as &lt;a href=\"demons\"&gt;demons&lt;/a&gt; and can be formidable opponents when in large groups. Their &lt;a href=\"Arrows\"&gt;Arrows&lt;/a&gt; stun and damage heroes from long ranges; allowing them to wear down adversaries before they can even close in for melee combat.\nWhen confronting Goatmen Archers it is best to deal with them quickly. This can be based on evasion. Another way to circumvent their arrows is to move out of sight once you stumble upon archers. As they can no longer see you, the archers will come after you. This way you can ambush them around corners, giving you the advantage of melee range.\nStats.\nWithin the game, Archers hail from several clans\u2014the &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Clan\"&gt;Flesh Clan&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Stone%20Clan\"&gt;Stone Clan&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Clan\"&gt;Fire Clan&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Night%20Clan\"&gt;Night Clan&lt;/a&gt;. They steadily increase in strength in the aforementioned order."}
{"id": "45502", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45502", "title": "Goatman Berserker", "text": "The Goatman Berserker is a type of &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; enemy in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThere are two forms of the Berseker. The core form is the &lt;a href=\"Moon%20Clan\"&gt;Moon Clan&lt;/a&gt; Berserker, found on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;. The second is the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Clan\"&gt;Ice Clan&lt;/a&gt; Fleshcarver, found in the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;. Both engage in melee and are much more powerful than their smaller breathren. They each have a &lt;a href=\"Berserk%20Charge%20%28monster%20skill%29\"&gt;charge attack&lt;/a&gt;, delivering &lt;a href=\"knockback\"&gt;knockback&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "31452", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31452", "title": "Goatman Brute", "text": "Goatman Brutes are a type of &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; enemy found in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDiablo Immortal.\nGoatman Brutes are basic khazra melee enemies. They are referred to as \"Brutes,\" with their clan coming first in their description (e.g. \"&lt;a href=\"Moon%20Clan\"&gt;Moon Clan&lt;/a&gt;) Brute. They attack with axes. \nMoon Clan Brutes are encountered in &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;, while &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Clan\"&gt;Ice Clan&lt;/a&gt; Warriors are encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;. Despite the name and weapon change (&lt;a href=\"maces\"&gt;maces&lt;/a&gt; in place of axes), Warriors are identical to Brutes.\nDiablo III.\nBrutes are encountered in , specifically the Highlands areas of the act, and are the grunts of the &lt;a href=\"Moon%20Clan\"&gt;Moon Clan&lt;/a&gt;. Armed with &lt;a href=\"axes\"&gt;axes&lt;/a&gt;, they are averagely powerful and attack in close combat. If a Brute makes it to a &lt;a href=\"Khazra%20Drum\"&gt;Khazra Drum&lt;/a&gt;, he will make all nearby khazra more resilient and powerful, but slow them down significantly.\nTheir &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Clan\"&gt;Blood Clan&lt;/a&gt; equivalents are &lt;a href=\"Goatman%20Mauler\"&gt;Goatman Mauler&lt;/a&gt;s.\n&lt;a href=\"Ice%20Clan\"&gt;Ice Clan&lt;/a&gt; Warriors are identical to Moon Clan ones, but have a slightly brighter coloring, and are encountered only in &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Ruins of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "11854", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11854", "title": "Goatman Impaler", "text": "Goatman Impalers (a.k.a. Goatman Slingers) are a ranged-attacking type of &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; enemy appearing in multiple games starting with \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They have a similar role to the &lt;a href=\"Goatman%20Archer\"&gt;Goatman Archer&lt;/a&gt;s of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDiablo III.\nImpalers made their debut in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They attack from range, wielding javelins in the style of &lt;a href=\"Slinger\"&gt;Lacuni Slingers&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are three types (&lt;a href=\"Moon%20Clan\"&gt;Moon Clan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Clan\"&gt;Ice Clan&lt;/a&gt; and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Blood%20Clan\"&gt;Blood Clan&lt;/a&gt;), but their differences are almost exclusively cosmetic (Blood Clan Impalers attack slightly faster). A typical ranged class, Goatman Impalers tend to stay on the back lines and support their comrades from afar. However, their spears fly slower than arrows, making them easier to dodge.\nDiablo Immortal.\nGoatmen Impalers appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", specifically on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; (representing the &lt;a href=\"Moon%20Clan\"&gt;Moon Clan&lt;/a&gt;) and &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt; (representing the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Clan\"&gt;Ice Clan&lt;/a&gt;). Apart from appearance, the Impalers of both clans function identically.\nDiablo IV.\nGoatman Impalers reappear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHeroes of the Storm.\nKhazra appear in the &lt;a href=\"http%3A//heroesofthestorm.wikia.com/wiki/Battlefield_of_Eternity\"&gt;Battlefield of Eternity&lt;/a&gt; map in \"&lt;a href=\"Heroes%20of%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Heroes of the Storm&lt;/a&gt;\", taking the place of siege giants. Their appearance is of Moon Clan Impalers."}
{"id": "31460", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31460", "title": "Goatman Mauler", "text": "Goatman Maulers are a type of &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; enemy encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nDiablo III.\nMaulers are the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Clan\"&gt;Blood Clan&lt;/a&gt; equivalent of &lt;a href=\"Goatman%20Brute\"&gt;Brutes&lt;/a&gt;, distinguished by their larger size and extra head. Their attacks inflict &lt;a href=\"Knockback\"&gt;Knockback&lt;/a&gt;, and they can enter Berserk mode, in which they deal more damage and move faster, but the effect ends after short time.\nDiablo IV.\nMaulers return in \"Diablo IV\"."}
{"id": "4673", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4673", "title": "Goatman Shaman", "text": "Goatman Shamans are a subtype of &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nLong ago, five clans of the &lt;a href=\"Umbaru\"&gt;Umbaru&lt;/a&gt; tribe left the &lt;a href=\"Teganze\"&gt;Teganze&lt;/a&gt; and ventured north. After their transformation into khazra, only a few elders were still able to use &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;, and they passed it down to their cleverest children. These became the khazra shaman, and they rank among the most dangerous of their race.\nThe shamans are not known for their loyalty, and will betray anyone at a whim.\nIn-game.\nDiablo Immortal.\nGoatman Shaman are present in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They mainly attack at range with a simple fire bolt (&lt;a href=\"Moon%20Clan\"&gt;Moon Clan&lt;/a&gt;) or frost bolt (&lt;a href=\"Ice%20Clan\"&gt;Ice Clan&lt;/a&gt;). They can also summon &lt;a href=\"totem\"&gt;totem&lt;/a&gt;s that buff their fellow khazra and deal continuous damage (&lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"cold\"&gt;cold&lt;/a&gt;) to the player in an area around them.\nDiablo III.\nGoatman Shamans were first encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn combat, Shamans attack with their staves, if cornered, but prefer to cast spells from afar.\nMoon Clan Shamans attack by launching erratically moving &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Orb\"&gt;Frozen Orb&lt;/a&gt;s that explode for &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; damage on impact, hitting a large area and Chilling enemies within.\u00a0\nIce Clan Shamans are identical, but instead of Frozen Orbs, conjure &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;fiery&lt;/a&gt; apparitions that travel forward, &lt;a href=\"piercing\"&gt;piercing&lt;/a&gt; through enemies and dealing Fire damage.\nBoth Ice and Moon Clan Shamans need roughly 2 seconds to charge their attacks, therefore they cannot fire it too often, giving player time to dodge the spell.\nBlood Clan Shamans (Sorcerers) gain Fireball attack (does not explode, but deals much more &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage than Cold sphere) and Spell Shield. The latter allows protecting one allied unit (but not the Shaman himself), making that ally 95% resistant to all damage types except &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0for several seconds. Killing the Shaman ends the effect, but remember that several Shamans can shield each other.\nShamans are rarely alone, often being supported by ambushing Goatman Brutes and Impalers.\nDiablo IV.\nThe Goatman Shaman reappears in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
