{"id": "34942", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34942", "title": "Goblin Defense", "text": "Goblin Defense is a cut &lt;a href=\"event\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It was designed during the second iteration of &lt;a href=\"Challenge%20Mode\"&gt;Challenge Mode&lt;/a&gt;, designed in reaction to positive reactions from the playerbase towards &lt;a href=\"Treasure%20Goblin\"&gt;Treasure Goblin&lt;/a&gt;s. It functions with various Goblins streaming towards a portal, with the player(s) trying to kill as many as possible before they escaped. The event was positively received from within the development team, with a sense of competition as to which player could kill the most Goblins."}
