{"id": "17400", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17400", "title": "Holus", "text": "Holus was the mayor of &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;. During the &lt;a href=\"End%20of%20Days\"&gt;End of Days&lt;/a&gt;, he met his end at &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nOnce a merchant who came to &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, Holus became mayor of the town soon after. While he was an adequate ruler of the town in times of peace, his bravery proved to be quite lacking when the &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Fallen Star&lt;/a&gt; hit the old &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;cathedral&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;dead&lt;/a&gt; began to rise to attack the town.\nThe Mayor, fearing for his life, tried to flee the town and take his broken cart with him, regardless of the blockage it caused. He claimed that the town was doomed and that anyone with a grain of sense would flee. His cowardice disgusted both the townsfolk and &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;, who refused to help him. Eventually, the townsfolk dragged his cart aside, leaving him to wallow in his despair before fleeing.\nMaking his living as a merchant once again, Holus made his way to Bastion's Keep, only to find the fortress under siege by &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. Here, he encountered The Nephalem again. Certain that if he stayed he would be slaughtered, he offered to pay the Nephalem anything if it would gain him an escort to safety. The Nephalem refused, and continued to do so as the siege progressed. Eventually, Holus rationalized that it was perhaps safer to stay and, if it came to it, fight. The Nephalem was taken by surprise by his change in attitude, surprised again when it was discovered that Holus had indeed stayed. As Holus stated, while he wasn't brave, he wasn't a liar.\nThe siege was thrown back and the demons defeated. However, &lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt; turned on the keep's defenders, killing many of them. Holus stood his ground and fought, a defiance which cost him his life.\nIn-game.\nHolus is encountered as an &lt;a href=\"NPCs\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; throughout \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn , Holus is designated as \"Mayor Holus,\" and can be found blocking the way into the rest of the town with his personal belongings in a cart. After the player visits the &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;Cathedral&lt;/a&gt; for the first time, his cart will be removed from the road, permitting the player to explore the rest of the town.\nUpon arriving in &lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt;, he can be found inside of &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt; once again cowering for his life. His name also slightly changes, gaining the title of \"Former Mayor.\" Through the act, he will often give foresight into the oncoming quest, and the hero will encourage him to be a braver man.\nImmediately after beginning &lt;a href=\"Act%20IV%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt;, if the player returns to Bastion's Keep, they can find his corpse in his previous location. A nearby guard will explain how he stood his ground till the very end."}
{"id": "26922", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26922", "title": "Holy", "text": "Holy is an &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Damage\"&gt;Elemental Damage&lt;/a&gt; type introduced in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", typically associated with white or golden color. It refers to divine power of &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;, and is mostly used by &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s, followers of &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; faith or by priests of other gods. In game, only &lt;a href=\"Crusader\"&gt;Crusader&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;s use this damage type. Previously in the \"Diablo\" series, most attacks that might now be considered Holy damage simply dealt &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Damage\"&gt;Magic Damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nHoly damage is subject to &lt;a href=\"Arcane\"&gt;Arcane&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"resistance\"&gt;resistance&lt;/a&gt; rather than having its own resistance value; this is sometimes known as Arcane/Holy resistance. This removes the need for players to pursue a resistance stat that very few monsters use, but which some do, such as &lt;a href=\"Raiziel\"&gt;Raiziel&lt;/a&gt;, as well as attacks from other players in &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll Holy skills also &lt;a href=\"Slain%20Monsters%20Rest%20in%20Peace\"&gt;destroy corpses&lt;/a&gt; of slain enemies, which for any other damage type only happens if killed by a &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt;. Holy skills cause the target to vanish in the flash of bright light, leaving nothing behind as if they were vaporized completely. However, this is is suppressed if there are reanimator monsters nearby.\nHoly damage does not have any special effect against the &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt;s, or any other \"dark magic\". However, many Holy skills &lt;a href=\"Blind\"&gt;Blind&lt;/a&gt; the target or heal the caster or their allies.\n,\u00a0, , &lt;a href=\"Akanesh\"&gt;Akanesh&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Scourge\"&gt;Golden Scourge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Skycutter\"&gt;Skycutter&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Swamp%20Land%20Waders\"&gt;Swamp Land Waders&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hallowed%20Barricade\"&gt;Hallowed Barricade&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0are the items with unconventional bonus to Holy skills damage. &lt;a href=\"Countess%20Julia%27s%20Cameo\"&gt;Countess Julia's Cameo&lt;/a&gt; amulet will render the character completely immune to both Holy and Arcane damage, and in fact such attacks will \"heal\" &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;)."}
