{"id": "20378", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20378", "title": "Holy Beacon", "text": "The Holy Beacon is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"amulets\"&gt;amulet&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 50 to drop.\nThis amulet is specifically designed for Holy &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;s, providing them with decent Holy damage bonus (up to 20% at level 70, which is as high as any other amulet), but can be of some use to Holy &lt;a href=\"Crusader\"&gt;Crusader&lt;/a&gt;s too. It is the only amulet that can increase Monk's &lt;a href=\"Spirit\"&gt;Spirit&lt;/a&gt; regeneration. If a Crusader is to use this, however, this Spirit regeneration should be the stat to get rid of through &lt;a href=\"Enchanting\"&gt;Enchanting&lt;/a&gt;, as otherwise, the amulet will effectively give them 3 Primary affixes."}
{"id": "3003", "revid": "48095951", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3003", "title": "Holy Bolt", "text": "Holy Bolt is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"The Paladin can learn to summon bolts formed of pure, righteous energies. These projectiles are vessels of life, bane to the undead, and succor to the faithful. At the battle of Taelohn Bridge, the villagers feared the day was lost when an army of the walking dead besieged them. Just as the battered militia was about to be overwhelmed, a small band of Paladins appeared. Wading through the rotting carcasses of the living dead and hurling spheres of pure &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; that expelled the evil controlling the battling corpses while renewing the strength of the remaining villagers.\"\nGeneral Information.\nHoly Bolt is unique in that it is both a &lt;a href=\"healing\"&gt;healing&lt;/a&gt; tool and a damaging skill. This is an improvement over the &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Bolt%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;original spell&lt;/a&gt;, which could only do damage.\nUnfortunately, its power is effective only against enemies of the &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt; subtype. While there is no shortage of Undead or Demon enemies on which this skill can be unleashed, it does not possess the raw damage potential of other skills (although this is compensated by completely ignoring enemies'\u00a0&lt;a href=\"resistances\"&gt;resistances&lt;/a&gt;). However, it is effective if you can get enemies lined up or you utilize chokepoints. As a healing power, Holy Bolt is still a sometimes useful utility skill, and can heal several hundred Life points per second if specialized accordingly.\nHoly Bolt was buffed in \"\".\nHoly Bolt does not heal Undead minions or allies, but it doesn't hurt them, either. The healing effect, however, works on &lt;a href=\"hirelings\"&gt;hirelings&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Golems\"&gt;Golems&lt;/a&gt;, and party members.\nHoly Bolt pierces targets, both hostile and friendly.\nDespite what D2R patch v2.4 notes say, the damage was \"not\" increased by 50% while the Blessed Hammer synergy was removed ."}
{"id": "10090", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10090", "title": "Holy Bolt (Diablo I)", "text": "Holy Bolt is a special &lt;a href=\"Holy\"&gt;Holy&lt;/a&gt; spell in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGeneral Information.\nHoly Bolt creates a bolt of holy energy dealing damage to &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;, bypassing &lt;a href=\"resistance\"&gt;resistance&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"immunities\"&gt;immunities&lt;/a&gt;. The higher the level, the faster the bolt travels. However, it does not scale damage with Spell Level, but with &lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Character Level&lt;/a&gt; instead.\nDamage Calculation: (Random 9-18) + Character Level\nThis spell does damage to &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; himself (quite considerable damage in vanilla \"Diablo I\", but much less in \"\"), although he is not actually Undead, but is completely useless against all other demons in game (&lt;a href=\"Bone%20Demon\"&gt;Bone Demon&lt;/a&gt;s, strangely, are unharmed by it). In return, it does not harm friendly targets either. The spell will simply pass through unaffected foes, without even alerting them to the caster's presence.\n may add +2 Spell levels to Holy Bolt, at permanent cost of 10% of base maximum Mana.\nLore.\n\"While the &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; were the greatest mortal spell casters ever known, not all of the followers of the Light were as proficient in magic as they were. During the quest to bind &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;, common soldiers were hard pressed to combat the seemingly endless tides of the undead that guarded the First Brother. During this time, &lt;a href=\"Cathan\"&gt;Cathan&lt;/a&gt;, a devout priest who was also a fierce warrior, found that by invoking the powers of the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt; and then infusing them with the essence of Fire, a bolt of great speed and intensity could be created and used by those otherwise untrained in the use of magic. This Holy Bolt harms only the undead, making it far safer to use while on a chaotic battlefield.\""}
