{"id": "3803", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3803", "title": "Holy Fire", "text": "Holy Fire is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"With a hint of brimstone in the air, the noble Paladin strides into battle encased in this holy aura. All those within its range are burnt with the fires of divine virtue. Beware, Beasts of Hell! The fire of purification is upon you!\"\nGeneral Information.\nHoly Fire is the first aura that adds &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Damage\"&gt;Elemental Damage&lt;/a&gt; to the Paladin's attack and deals periodic damage to enemies near the Paladin. At high levels, this skill rapidly kills entire screens of &lt;a href=\"Monsters\"&gt;Monsters&lt;/a&gt; in early &lt;a href=\"Normal%20difficulty\"&gt;Normal difficulty&lt;/a&gt;.\nDamage scales based on distance to the caster. Aura deals double damage at melee range and linearly scales to normal damage at maximum range. The displayed maximum Area Damage value incorporates the maximum proximity damage bonus.\nHoly Fire is rarely used elsewhere due to its rather low damage potential and it being generally outclassed by &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Shock\"&gt;Holy Shock&lt;/a&gt;. It mainly finds use with niche builds like so-called Rangers, Paladins who use any &lt;a href=\"Missile%20Weapon\"&gt;missile weapon&lt;/a&gt; which shoots &lt;a href=\"Exploding%20Arrow\"&gt;Exploding Arrow&lt;/a&gt;s as their main &lt;a href=\"Weapons\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt;. The Aura's Fire &lt;a href=\"Damage\"&gt;Damage&lt;/a&gt; is actually added to the area-effect explosions and can be quite high when fully synergized.\n&lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Golem\"&gt;Fire Golem&lt;/a&gt; inherently has this Aura.\nThere are also a few &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; that give this Aura, including the &lt;a href=\"runeword\"&gt;runeword&lt;/a&gt;s and ."}
{"id": "3190", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3190", "title": "Holy Freeze", "text": "Holy Freeze is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Using this aura, the Paladin causes the temperature of the air around him to drop drastically, &lt;a href=\"Freeze\"&gt;freezing&lt;/a&gt; the flesh of his enemies. Those so affected will find their movement drastically hindered and are easily dispatched back to the Hells from whence they spawned.\"\nGeneral Information.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Fire\"&gt;Holy Fire&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Shock\"&gt;Holy Shock&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0this deals periodic damage to all enemies near the user. While it deals about half the damage of Holy Shock, Holy Freeze also slows most enemies in its radius, making it a powerful survival tool.\nDamage scales based on distance to the caster. Aura deals double damage at melee range and linearly scales to normal damage at maximum range. The displayed maximum Area Damage value incorporates the maximum proximity damage bonus.\nAlthough graphically it is identical to &lt;a href=\"chill\"&gt;chill&lt;/a&gt;ing, it is actually mechanically different: it works on even cold &lt;a href=\"immune\"&gt;immune&lt;/a&gt; enemies, and it stacks with chilling on enemies vulnerable to cold, &lt;a href=\"Decrepify\"&gt;Decrepify&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Clay%20Golem\"&gt;Clay Golem&lt;/a&gt;'s effects to create an extremely potent slowdown.\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Cold%20Resistance\"&gt;Cold Resistance&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cannot%20Be%20Frozen\"&gt;Cannot Be Frozen&lt;/a&gt; Items do not have any effect on Holy Freeze.\nThe Defensive &lt;a href=\"Desert%20Mercenary\"&gt;Desert Mercenary&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Nightmare\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt; comes with this aura. This is often the ideal choice for characters who do not benefit from &lt;a href=\"Might\"&gt;Might&lt;/a&gt; (or a particularly damaging mercenary), especially if the character lacks other effective methods of crowd control.\nThere are also a few &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; that give this Aura, including the &lt;a href=\"runeword\"&gt;runeword&lt;/a&gt;s and .\n&lt;a href=\"Duriel\"&gt;Duriel&lt;/a&gt; also makes use of this skill. The combination of his Holy Freeze, high speed, and high damage makes him a dangerous boss for this reason.\nEven though this aura chills even some monsters that are immune to cold, some monsters are still immune to the effects of slowing. Monsters that have a value of 0 for Chilling Effect simply are not affected at all. Many of these \"monsters\" are immobile defense-type enemies in which chilling makes less sense anyway. All enemies with 0 (or less) chilling include:"}
{"id": "21043", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21043", "title": "Holy Point Shot", "text": "The Holy Point Shot is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quivers\"&gt;quiver&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Hunter\"&gt;Demon Hunter&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;. It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 29 to drop.\nIt is the only quiver with bonus to elemental skill damage.\nAs of patch 2.5.0, it gained a unique Legendary affix: throws not one, but 3 knives. Additional knives are thrown at each side, with roughly 30 degrees spread.\nAs of patch 2.6.9, it also increases Impale damage."}
{"id": "26780", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26780", "title": "Holy Sanctum", "text": "Holy Sanctum is a small dungeon that can be found in &lt;a href=\"Gardens%20of%20Hope\"&gt;Gardens of Hope&lt;/a&gt; 2nd and 3rd Tier in &lt;a href=\"Act%20IV%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nInside, an named &lt;a href=\"Watch%20Your%20Step\"&gt;Watch Your Step&lt;/a&gt; is guaranteed to occur, if the zone itself appears.\n&lt;a href=\"Town%20Portal\"&gt;Town Portal&lt;/a&gt; cannot be used within the Holy Sanctum, possibly because the unstable ground of the Watch Your Step event would cause potential problems. There is no restriction on leaving the Sanctum, using Town Portal, then re-entering it."}
{"id": "3009", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3009", "title": "Holy Shield", "text": "Holy Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"To a Paladin, the shield is a symbol of his faith. Particularly devout Paladins can channel their faith into their shields, bolstering its defensive value with holy energy. The purer his faith, the greater his defense.\"\nGeneral Information.\nOne of the Paladin's most important and often-used skills, Holy Shield greatly increases a user's chance to &lt;a href=\"block\"&gt;block&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Smite\"&gt;Smite&lt;/a&gt; damage, and total &lt;a href=\"Defense\"&gt;Defense&lt;/a&gt; from all sources, including &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;. Holy Shield is a personal buff similar to the &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress'&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Armor\"&gt;Frozen Armor&lt;/a&gt; line of spells and the &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%27s\"&gt;Necromancer's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Armor\"&gt;Bone Armor&lt;/a&gt; spell. It costs a large amount of &lt;a href=\"Mana\"&gt;Mana&lt;/a&gt; and, at lower levels, the duration isn't very long; however, more points allocated in this skill will increase its duration and power, effectively making it a passive enhancement.\nThe defense increase listed for this skill multiplies the total Defense the user has, not just that of the shield.\nThe skill effect still remains active even if weapons are swapped. Therefore, if the user's secondary set has better bonuses to Combat Skills and/or Holy Shield, he/she can activate Holy Shield with that set and then swap back to their main set with a better enhancement to their shield than one would have earned by casting the skill using your primary equipment.\nHoly Shield effectively lowers the effectiveness of the &lt;a href=\"Thorns\"&gt;Thorns&lt;/a&gt; Aura, which only activates when foes successfully hit users.\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 35"}
{"id": "3801", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3801", "title": "Holy Shock", "text": "Holy Shock is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"A Paladin blessed with the power of this aura calls upon the power of the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; to strike forth at all enemies surrounding him. Divine bolts spring from the earth to smite the Paladin's enemies.\"\nGeneral Information.\nAlthough the minimum damage of Holy Shock is low, it has the highest maximum and average damage out of the three pulse damage auras. Players investing heavily in this skill and its synergies can often simply walk by crowds of enemies and watch them all die without lifting a finger in &lt;a href=\"Normal%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Normal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;. Towards &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; this will likely no longer be the case, but the aura also adds a very high amount of lightning damage to weapon attacks, so when combined with a fast weapon (and preferably &lt;a href=\"Zeal\"&gt;Zeal&lt;/a&gt;), the player can still easily cut through any enemies not immune to lightning.\nDamage scales based on distance to the caster. Aura deals double damage at melee range and linearly scales to normal damage at maximum range. The displayed maximum Area Damage value incorporates the maximum proximity damage bonus.\nThere are also a few &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; that give this Aura, including the &lt;a href=\"runeword\"&gt;runeword&lt;/a&gt; ."}
