{"id": "42967", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42967", "title": "Horadric Legacy", "text": "Horadric Legacy is a &lt;a href=\"cosmetic%20set\"&gt;cosmetic set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Per its namesake, it is themed around &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis cosmetic set was awarded to all players that pre-registered for \"Diablo Immortal\" as a reward to celebrate over 30 million pre-orders for the game.\nThe cosmetic for the class was released as a reward for completing the &lt;a href=\"Dread%20Pilgrimage\"&gt;Dread Pilgrimage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe cosmetic for the &lt;a href=\"Tempest\"&gt;Tempest&lt;/a&gt; class was released as one of the reward for playing the &lt;a href=\"Deluged%20Plane\"&gt;Deluged Plane&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3407", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3407", "title": "Horadric Malus", "text": "The Horadric Malus is an enchanted smithing hammer.\nLore.\nThe Horadric Malus is an enchanted smithing hammer that forged and enchanted by &lt;a href=\"Horadric\"&gt;Horadric&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;s, which they used to forge enchanted armaments for their struggle against the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt;. When their union dissolved, the Malus was entrusted to the &lt;a href=\"Sisterhood%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sisterhood of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;Centuries later&lt;/a&gt;, the Malus was in the possession of &lt;a href=\"Charsi\"&gt;Charsi&lt;/a&gt;. She left it behind when she and the Sisterhood were forced to flee &lt;a href=\"Eastgate%20Keep\"&gt;Eastgate Keep&lt;/a&gt;. When the forces of &lt;a href=\"Andariel\"&gt;Andariel&lt;/a&gt; took control the Monastery, the Malus was entrusted to &lt;a href=\"the%20Smith\"&gt;the Smith&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Barracks\"&gt;Barracks&lt;/a&gt;. It was retrieved by a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter Charsi left the Sisterhood, she kept the Malus, using it at her &lt;a href=\"Charsi%27s%20Smithy\"&gt;forge&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Malus quest item needed to complete the &lt;a href=\"Tools%20of%20the%20Trade\"&gt;Tools of the Trade&lt;/a&gt; quest in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". It has powers rivaling the &lt;a href=\"Hell%20Forge%20Hammer\"&gt;Hell Forge Hammer&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Horadric Malus can only be retrieved from its stand by a character that is at least level 8 and has not yet completed the quest. The Horadric Malus also cannot be picked up until after Deckard Cain has been rescued from Tristram. It is thoroughly unremarkable as a weapon, and is much better used to complete the quest.\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: 6 To 16\nDurability: 66\nRequired Strength: 16\nRequired Dexterity: 16\nMace Class - \nDevelopment.\nIn the russian.txt from game files there is an entry named: Nirom Malus. It is not known what this may reference, possibly the name of the hammer's creator, or the full name of the hammer itself."}
