{"id": "39148", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39148", "title": "Horde of the Ninety Savages", "text": "Horde of the Ninety Savages\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", added in patch 2.6.8.\nIt is named after the titular &lt;a href=\"Horde%20of%20the%20Ninety%20Savages%20%28Lore%29\"&gt;tribe&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe set requires a character level of 70 and can only be equipped by the Barbarian class. This set can only drop at &lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; difficulty.\nPieces.\nThe set consists of six pieces. All six are required to complete the set, and all of them are Barbarian-restricted.\nSet Bonus:\nFor the first bonus, includes &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Rage\"&gt;Battle Rage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Threatening%20Shout\"&gt;Threatening Shout&lt;/a&gt; and , doubling all of their basic \"and\" rune effects, excluding the duration (there is an &lt;a href=\"Inspiring%20Presence\"&gt;Inspiring Presence&lt;/a&gt; passive for that, though). The double damage effect is multiplicative to other similar modifiers and applies to any source of Fear/Freeze/Stun.\nThe second and third bonuses allow for a Primary skill-centered set. &lt;a href=\"Simplicity%27s%20Strength\"&gt;Simplicity's Strength&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Oathkeeper\"&gt;Oathkeeper&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Depth%20Diggers\"&gt;Depth Diggers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Undisputed%20Champion\"&gt;The Undisputed Champion&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Revered\"&gt;Bastion's Revered&lt;/a&gt; are recommended to enhance it further."}
