{"id": "44282", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44282", "title": "Horrorspawn", "text": "s are a type of &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28monster%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Silent%20Monastery\"&gt;Silent Monastery&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nHorrorspawns are mangled necromantic constructs made by the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20of%20the%20Nightmare\"&gt;Guardian of the Nightmare&lt;/a&gt; from the remains of sacrificed victims fused with at least a &lt;a href=\"Clawed%20Gorgon\"&gt;Clawed Gorgon&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Hateborn%20Reaver\"&gt;Hateborn Reaver&lt;/a&gt;s per victim..\nThe horrorspawns bear features reminiscent of their constituents\u2014curved blades from the Hateborn Reavers, four legged gait from the Clawed Gorgon and human hands from the human sacrifice. When exposed to &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;, the horrorspawns separate into its components. The &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; base is already tainted and twisted into spawnlings, which look like a miniature version of the horrorspawn.\nIn-game.\nSo far, s have only been encountered at the Silent Monastery. They attack with either claw &lt;a href=\"swipe\"&gt;swipe&lt;/a&gt;s from their hands or from one of the four scything blades at the edges of their heads. They can make a &lt;a href=\"Berserk%20Charge\"&gt;Berserk Charge&lt;/a&gt;, clawing and cutting anything in their path, or suck air into their mouths to create a that draws their next victim to themselves."}
