{"id": "52674", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52674", "title": "Howler's Call", "text": " is a 5-star &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Gem\"&gt;Legendary Gem&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "50400", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50400", "title": "Howler Hunt", "text": "Howler Hunt is a limited-time \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" event. It is similar to &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Among_Us\"&gt;Among Us&lt;/a&gt;, which is based on the parlour game \"Werewolf\".\nGameplay.\nHowler Hunt becomes available from &lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Level&lt;/a&gt; 30. The player is tasked with obtaining Sacred Energy from Sacred Wards and submitting it to the Altar of Purging, located at the center of the map. During the match, one of the player's companions will become The Howler. The Howler is tasked with sabotaging their former companions' progress, using additional threats to their advantage to disrupt any progress made. Howlers can summon Undead Incursions and blighted Sacred Wards to cause chaos and sow the seeds of dissent from the shadows.\nEmbodying the night terror of The Howler presents unbridled advantages, but those that can master their lunar urges will reign supreme. Howlers can instantly slay their nearest ally, but this will reveal their true Howler form for several seconds. Subsequent kills create longer cooldown times, so feast on your companions wisely.\nOnce a slain adventurer's corpse is located, a vote will be called to execute the adventurer suspected of the foul deed.\nAdventurers and the treacherous Howler win through different means. If all Howlers are executed successfully through a vote, the Adventurers succeed in their grim task. Similarly, if the Howlers manage to execute all Adventurers, the night is theirs. If the Sacred Energy bar reaches 100% completion, the Adventurers win. If all Sacred Wards are destroyed, the Howlers win.\nRewards are determined by how much you assist\u2014or deter\u2014the player side\u2019s victory. Collecting and turning in Sacred Energy, participating in voting your fellow Adventurers out, slaying Adventurers as the Howler and dealing with threats will contribute to rewards.\nHistory.\nHowler Hunt was first available between January 31, 3 a.m.\u2013February 21, 3 a.m., 2024. It returned for the 2024 &lt;a href=\"Hallow%27s%20Wake\"&gt;Hallow's Wake&lt;/a&gt; event."}
