{"id": "34250", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34250", "title": "Humbart Wessel", "text": "Humbart Wessel is a talking skull, and companion of the &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Zayl\"&gt;Zayl&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nJourney to Ureh.\nIn life, Humbart was a veteran fighter from &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, making a living as a mercenary captain. In the year &lt;a href=\"Timeline%23c.%20-736\"&gt;-736&lt;/a&gt;, he traveled with &lt;a href=\"Gregus%20Mazi\"&gt;Gregus Mazi&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Ureh\"&gt;Ureh&lt;/a&gt;. On the seventh day, Mazi again approached the edge of the city's ruins. Humbart told him that the quest was helpless and they should just leave, but Mazi remained steadfast. Humbart was skeptical of Mazi's claims of reaching Ureh and entering &lt;a href=\"Heaven\"&gt;Heaven&lt;/a&gt;, but sure enough, a shimmer occurred, and the ruins appeared 'alive.' Lights even glowed from them. Mazi disappeared before their eyes as he entered the shadow of the city. Neither Humbart or his men would follow the &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;. The mercenaries camped outside the ruins. They heard voices coming from them, as if calling to them, but none of them would enter. He told his mercenary company that when Mazi came out the following day, they'd go in and get their fill. But tomorrow came, and there were no ruins, no lights, no voices, and no Gregus Mazi.\nPer a prior agreement with Lord &lt;a href=\"Hyram\"&gt;Hyram&lt;/a&gt;, Humbart recorded his experiences and sent it to the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt;.\nResurrection.\nLong after Humbart's death, Zayl the Necromancer resurrected him to find what information he could on Ureh. Somehow, he never got round to sending Humbart's spirit back to the &lt;a href=\"Plane%20of%20the%20Dead\"&gt;Plane of the Dead&lt;/a&gt;. Humbart, apparently content with (un)life as a talking skull, was in no hurry to be sent back. Zayl ensorcelled\u00a0the warrior's skull and made it his personal companion and magical off-hand tool, keeping Humbart inside his belt pouch.\nReaper of Souls.\nHumbart was with Zayl as he entered the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Marsh\"&gt;Blood Marsh&lt;/a&gt;, in a bid to fix the imbalance in the area. The pair encountered &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;. Despite Zayl telling Humbart to be quiet, he told the Nephalem that if Zayl had been in the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20Rakkis\"&gt;Tomb of Rakkis&lt;/a&gt; when &lt;a href=\"Malthael\"&gt;Malthael&lt;/a&gt; had come to retrieve the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Soulstone\"&gt;Black Soulstone&lt;/a&gt;, he wouldn't have succeeded. The Nephalem told them of their intention to kill &lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt;. Humbart decided the matter to be settled, and that they should go get a drink.\nIn-game.\nHumbart appears as both an NPC and pet in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nNPC.\nHumbart appears in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", carried by Zayl. He himself isn't clickable in the same way as a standard NPC is, but will chime in when the player converses with Zayl."}
