{"id": "18804", "revid": "5449468", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18804", "title": "Hungering Arrow", "text": "Hungering Arrow is a skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is based on the classic &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; skills like &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Arrow\"&gt;Magic Arrow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Guided%20Arrow\"&gt;Guided Arrow&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nA magically-imbued arrow flies faster and may home at enemy (making rather sharp angle turns to hit its target). It is very effective when firing off-screen or firing blind.\nThe first enemy the arrow hits will suffer &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage, and there is also a chance that the arrow will pierce through the enemy, continuing its flight (it may even turn around 180 degrees and hit the same target again) with same damage on hit and same chances to pierce again. The cycle can repeat, until the pierce check fails.\nGenerates &lt;a href=\"Hatred\"&gt;Hatred&lt;/a&gt; even if it does not hit anything (but only once per arrow)."}
{"id": "42165", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42165", "title": "Hungering Echo", "text": "Hungering Echoes are &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s found in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", in the &lt;a href=\"A%20Mirrored%20World\"&gt;A Mirrored World&lt;/a&gt; zone. \nLore.\nThe Echoes are capable of speech, but (appear to) speak backwards. They claimed that a rune taken from the &lt;a href=\"Statue%20of%20Resurgence\"&gt;Statue of Resurgence&lt;/a&gt; sustained them, and when a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero/group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; retrieved it, tried to slay them. However, they were defeated, and the rune was taken back into &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "43049", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43049", "title": "Hungering Moon", "text": "The Hungering Moon is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; (of sorts) in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe Moon is a generous entity, and rewards its most faithful followers handsomely.\nGameplay.\nThe Hungering Moon was first introduced in &lt;a href=\"Season%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; 2 of \"Diablo Immortal\", and has returned on a regular basis. During the periods where the Moon is active, players can acquire &lt;a href=\"moonsliver\"&gt;moonsliver&lt;/a&gt;s and trade them in for blessings. Every seven blessings can be traded in for a random reward. The Moon interface can be accessed through the \"Events\" tab of the game's menu.\nThe event runs from 3 a.m. on a Saturday until 3 a.m. on the next Friday. Players can complete up to three tasks a day four times. Through completing tasks, they'll gain Astrolabe Power\u2014the power can be used to draw one of two types of blessings with unique benefits from the Astrolabe.\nThe blessings are as follows, with the moonsliver rewards:\nIf the dungeon is completed in a party first, the solo reward is also awarded.\nThe Hermit's Collection (located within the Hungering Moon event tab) can be accessed to trade moonslivers for lunar-laced rewards. Collecting and using 12 blessings in total earns The Moon's Regard\u2014a bounty of 90 bonus moonslivers.\nThe Hungering Moon will reward players with the following materials if they collect the listed amount of moonslivers during the event's duration. No moonslivers need to be spent to acquire the materials:\nMoonslivers can be spent on the following rewards:\nCompleting all the tasks (including taking the Moon's Regard) rewards exactly enough moonslivers to buy all the rewards.\nHistory.\nThe Seal of Triumph rewards were added with the release of &lt;a href=\"Event%20Center%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Event Center&lt;/a&gt;, with Hungering Moon running between May 4 and 11."}
