{"id": "17127", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17127", "title": "Hungry Corpse", "text": "Hungry Corpses\u00a0(a.k.a. Walking Corpses) are &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"monsters\"&gt;monsters&lt;/a&gt; found in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". \nIn-game.\nDiablo Immortal.\nHungry Corpses appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", at &lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Cemetery\"&gt;Ashwold Cemetery&lt;/a&gt;. They can also spit out globs of putrid bile which deal &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; damage.\nDiablo III.\nHungry Corpses are found in , , and . They are faster, tougher and stronger than average &lt;a href=\"Risen%20Dead\"&gt;risens&lt;/a&gt;, but are far fewer in number. One can easily recognize them by their more massive physique. They still share their lesser cousins' intelligence however and often shamble around aimlessly.\nThey often hide in the surroundings, and can crawl out of barrels and pits to ambush the player. Some of these sources of Corpses may be destroyed.\nHungry Corpses will sometimes spawn a &lt;a href=\"Crawling%20Torso\"&gt;Crawling Torso&lt;/a&gt; if not critically damaged."}
