{"id": "33631", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33631", "title": "Iben Fahd", "text": "Iben Fahd was a member of the original &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nThe Ammuit.\nIben Fahd was once a member of the &lt;a href=\"Ammuit%20Clan\"&gt;Ammuit Clan&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Morrick\"&gt;Morrick&lt;/a&gt; was his superior.\nFahd accepted his superior's invitation to the pit fights he hosted in &lt;a href=\"Gea%20Kul\"&gt;Gea Kul&lt;/a&gt;. At night, after the fight had concluded and the pit vacated, Fahd found his eye drawn to commingled &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; and sweat in the pit. He watched a puddle sink through a concavity in the ground. When it dripped below, he saw white teeth gleam in a glistening red snout. The blood vanished with a puff of sand and a guzzling noise.\nAt some point, the Ammuit stripped Fahd of his titles. He did not complain, but simply defected (it is unclear if this defection was to the &lt;a href=\"Ennead\"&gt;Ennead&lt;/a&gt; or Horadrim).\nThe Horadrim.\nFahd was one of the founding members of the Horadrim. He was one to first realize the dangers &lt;a href=\"Kanai%27s%20Cube\"&gt;Kanai's Cube&lt;/a&gt; posed, and spoke to the nine Horadrim against its further use, convincing most of them to hide the Cube.\nTal Rasha was among the Horadrim that bound their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; into &lt;a href=\"vessels\"&gt;vessels&lt;/a&gt;. As the Horadrim could not conquer &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;, these vessels would store their memories for future Horadrim.\nSometime after the Hunt for the Three, Fahd came to lead the Horadrim. Fahd participated in assault on &lt;a href=\"the%20Archives%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;the Archives of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. His most significant task was to carry &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;'s still-living head and &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; away, and hide them as far as he can (in &lt;a href=\"Desolate%20Sands\"&gt;Desolate Sands&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt;). He succeeded in sealing these in the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Ruins\"&gt;Forgotten Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vault%20of%20the%20Assassin\"&gt;Vault of the Assassin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cave%20of%20the%20Betrayer\"&gt;Cave of the Betrayer&lt;/a&gt;, hoping that the world will never disturb neither the head nor the deranged wizard's blood.\nCenturies later, the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt; contacted a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero&lt;/a&gt;, and guided them to the &lt;a href=\"Sanctum%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;sanctum&lt;/a&gt; of the real Fahd, narrating how the Horadrim had taken steps to ensure that others would follow in their footsteps.\nIn-game.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt; is encountered as an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", per the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; system.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", several of the &lt;a href=\"Kanai%27s%20Cube\"&gt;Kanai's Cube&lt;/a&gt; recipes bear his name: Anger, Pleasure, Wrath and Regret of Iben Fahd. His &lt;a href=\"Hunter%27s%20Journal\"&gt;journal&lt;/a&gt; can be found in ."}
{"id": "42408", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42408", "title": "Iben Fahd's Sanctum", "text": "Iben Fahd's Sanctum (a.k.a. the Sanctum of Iben Fahd) is a zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThe Sanctum was created by the original &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt;. During the &lt;a href=\"Hunt%20for%20the%20Three\"&gt;Hunt for the Three&lt;/a&gt;, the leaders of the Horadrim gathered her and imbued their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; into &lt;a href=\"vessels\"&gt;vessels&lt;/a&gt;, storing their memories and power for future Horadrim. These became manifest in 'living memories.' A &lt;a href=\"portal%20device\"&gt;portal device&lt;/a&gt; (or something similar) was built under the land where &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; would be constructed hundreds of years later, which led to the sanctum. Inside the sanctum, the Horadrim trained in the Aspirants' Grounds.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt; guided a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero&lt;/a&gt; to the Sanctum, deeming them fit to carry the legacy of the Horadrim.\nIn-game.\nThe Sanctum appears in \"Diablo Immortal\", and is unlocked during the \"\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. It is classified as a Westmarch zone, but appears to be far away from Westmarch itself. It is here that players use the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; system.\nMonsters.\nThe monsters appear outside the sanctum proper, inside the Aspirants' Grounds.\nChests.\nChests can be found after going through the dungeon section. They must be opened using &lt;a href=\"Aspirant%27s%20Key\"&gt;Aspirant's Key&lt;/a&gt;s. There are 5 chests per room and 4 rooms total, with some mobs spawning in between. The first chest can be opened for free, and each successive chest requires more keys to open. After opening all 20 chests, a secret chest shows up in the middle.\nIn the below table, the free chest's stones are not counted towards the cumulative rewards since the chest doesn't require any keys to open, whereas the final chest can be opened for free, but only after opening all 20 chests, so its reward is added to the 20th chest's reward.\nSince the ratio between stones and keys goes down and down, there is no point in saving keys for a single big run.\nHistory.\nThe update on added the ability to reset the vessel upgrades and unlock up to 10 levels with a single click."}
{"id": "43701", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43701", "title": "Iben Fahd's Tenacity", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"vessel\"&gt;vessel&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", and part of the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; system.\nPlayers can obtain it through unlocking &lt;a href=\"chests\"&gt;chests&lt;/a&gt; in the Aspirants' Grounds in &lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd%27s%20Sanctum\"&gt;Iben Fahd's Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;. The vessel spawns randomly."}
{"id": "4441", "revid": "839260", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4441", "title": "Ice", "text": ""}
{"id": "17376", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17376", "title": "Ice Armor", "text": "Ice Armor\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; spell used by\u00a0s in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It bears some resemblance to the classic &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt; skills &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Armor\"&gt;Frozen Armor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shiver%20Armor\"&gt;Shiver Armor&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chilling%20Armor\"&gt;Chilling Armor&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nIce Armor counts as an Armor spell, and only one Armor can be active at a time. It is arguably the most risky of the three Armor spells available to the Wizard, as it only takes effect in melee combat. However, it can be a useful skill for melee-orientated Wizards. &lt;a href=\"Chill\"&gt;Chill&lt;/a&gt; slows enemies' &lt;a href=\"movement%20speed\"&gt;movement speed&lt;/a&gt; by 60%, triggers if the attacker cannot be &lt;a href=\"frozen\"&gt;frozen&lt;/a&gt;, or if they have been recently frozen by Ice Armor.\nThe damage reduction only applies to melee attacks, including ground-based monster affixes."}
{"id": "38649", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38649", "title": "Ice Armor (Diablo IV)", "text": "Ice Armor\u00a0is a Defensive Cold passive skill used by \u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". Unlike similar classic spells, it is completely passive.\nIn-game.\nThis skill works almost exactly like the &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt; passive ability &lt;a href=\"Galvanizing%20Ward\"&gt;Galvanizing Ward&lt;/a&gt;: instead of increasing &lt;a href=\"Defense\"&gt;Armor&lt;/a&gt;, it plainly puts an &lt;a href=\"Absorption\"&gt;Absorption&lt;/a&gt; shield on the Sorceress. Its potency is restored to full after not taking any damage (even fully absorbed) for 5 seconds. Ranking the spell up lowers the recharge period. &lt;a href=\"Immunity\"&gt;Immunity&lt;/a&gt; to damage allows taking hits without resetting the timer.\nIt is the first Cold Armor spell in the series that does not &lt;a href=\"Chill\"&gt;Chill&lt;/a&gt; enemies on impact."}
{"id": "49731", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49731", "title": "Ice Armor (Diablo Immortal)", "text": "Ice Armor is a skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "2949", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2949", "title": "Ice Arrow", "text": "Ice Arrow is an &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". An upgrade over the &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Arrow\"&gt;Cold Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, it deals more cold damage and can freeze monsters.\nLore.\n\"The second of the prizes &lt;a href=\"Karcheus\"&gt;Karcheus&lt;/a&gt; bestows to a true &lt;a href=\"warrior\"&gt;warrior&lt;/a&gt;, this skill enables the Amazon to instill her arrows with the glacial force of a fierce blizzard. Enemies struck by this power not only feel the icy sting of the enchanted shaft, but also the force of a chilling arctic wind that, mysteriously, they alone can feel. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nWhile Ice Arrow completely freezes most targets, other players and elite enemies (such as &lt;a href=\"Champion%20monsters\"&gt;Champion monsters&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique Monsters&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Act%20Boss\"&gt;Act Boss&lt;/a&gt;es) are only\u00a0&lt;a href=\"slow\"&gt;slow&lt;/a&gt;ed rather than getting frozen when they are hit with this spell.\nAlthough freezing an enemy is overall useful, the damage and range of this skill is completely outclassed by &lt;a href=\"Freezing%20Arrow\"&gt;Freezing Arrow&lt;/a&gt;. Ice Arrow's main advantage over Freezing Arrow is that extra skill points increase the freeze duration, allowing the Amazon to halt an enemy for far longer than Freezing Arrow allows her to."}
{"id": "16731", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16731", "title": "Ice Arrow (magic suffix)", "text": "Ice Arrow is a &lt;a href=\"suffix\"&gt;suffix&lt;/a&gt; that can appear on &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;. It provides &lt;a href=\"Charged%20item\"&gt;charges&lt;/a&gt; of the skill &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Arrow\"&gt;Ice Arrow&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt can start spawning on items at &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; 36, but will not be able to spawn on all items until level 72.\nStats.\n\"Can appear on:\" &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;\n\"Is available on:\" &lt;a href=\"Amazon%20Weapons\"&gt;Amazon Bows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;Bows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crossbows\"&gt;Crossbows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gloves\"&gt;Gloves&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "38729", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38729", "title": "Ice Blades", "text": "Ice Blades\u00a0are a Conjuration Cold spell used by\u00a0 in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nThis spell is not cast at a specific target, and the blades cannot be aimed manually, instead seeking their own targets to hit."}
{"id": "2899", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2899", "title": "Ice Blast", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDescription.\n\"The freezing damage of this spell can shatter an opponent into icy shards, leaving enemy spellcasters little material with which to resurrect their minions. In this way the Sorceress can make quick work of those who would use the dead against her. \"\nGeneral Information.\nAn upgrade to &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Bolt\"&gt;Ice Bolt&lt;/a&gt;, and an intermediate spell to &lt;a href=\"Glacial%20Spike\"&gt;Glacial Spike&lt;/a&gt;, Ice Blast is a powerful &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; projectile that \"always\" &lt;a href=\"Freeze\"&gt;Freeze&lt;/a&gt;s an individual enemy completely solid. Not only does this render enemies unable to fight back, but frozen enemies shatter when killed, preventing them from being resurrected. This is useful when fighting enemies like &lt;a href=\"Fallen\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s.\nKeep in mind that in comparison to Glacial Spike, no one is necessarily clean cut better or worse; although Glacial Spike is cast faster and has a radius of impact, Ice Blast does more individual damage and has a much longer Freeze duration. Since they synergize with each other, Sorceresses specializing in Cold Spells may find it prudent to put points into both.\nOther players, bosses, super unique monsters, and champions will be &lt;a href=\"chill\"&gt;chill&lt;/a&gt;ed and not frozen when hit with Ice Blast."}
