{"id": "44252", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44252", "title": "Icehowl Ruins", "text": "Icehowl Ruins is a &lt;a href=\"Fractured%20Peaks\"&gt;Fractured Peaks&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dungeon%20%28Diablo%20IV%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt; available in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It is located \nnorth of &lt;a href=\"Nevesk\"&gt;Nevesk&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Icehowl%20Taiga\"&gt;Icehowl Taiga&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nA tower, Icehowl Ruins are located north of &lt;a href=\"Nevesk\"&gt;Nevesk&lt;/a&gt;. In &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, they were used by the villagers (who'd become enthralled by &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt;) to deposit the body of their village's &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt; priest. They carried out numerous sacrifices within the ruins, summoning &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. The ruins became overrun with demons, and were saturated with demonic &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe ruins were successfully cleared by .\nGameplay.\nIcehowl Ruins features in the game's , and is compulsory to complete as part of the \"&lt;a href=\"Darkness%20Within\"&gt;Darkness Within&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;."}
