{"id": "45182", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45182", "title": "Ichthid", "text": "Ichthids are amphibious &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;animal&lt;/a&gt;s that are commonly found in swamps or oases. \nLore.\nFor amphibious creatures, ichthids possess an unusually high concentration of serrated teeth. They can appear in any wet environment, preceded by the smell of muddy bile, and followed by a trail of carcasses nibbled into unrecognizability.\nIchthids can grow to massive sizes. Their skin is remarkably tough, despite having the consistency of wet mud. Mature male ichthids grow thin, hardened scales on their tail. In the largest sizes, these scales become crystalline. \nCrystalline scales of an Ichthid are tougher than steel, and can be used to make armor. Their skins form part of the recipe for &lt;a href=\"Clarity%27s%20Bane%20%28Potion%29\"&gt;Clarity's Bane&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn Bilefen, the &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Wetlands\"&gt;Northern Wetlands&lt;/a&gt; are the Ichthids' breeding ground.\nIn-game.\nIchthids are a type of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be found at &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Oasis%20of%20No%20Return\"&gt;Oasis of No Return&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt;."}
