{"id": "48330", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48330", "title": "Idol of the Faithful", "text": "The Idol of the Faithful is a &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt; artifact. It is cursed, sapping the strength and dulling the senses of whoever bears it.\nIt is used in the pilgrimage penitents undertake across the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Judgment\"&gt;Fields of Judgment&lt;/a&gt;, where they carry the idol on their back and come to shrines over the glacier. Reading from parchments located at these shrines removes the idol of its curse. The idol's final resting place is the &lt;a href=\"Shrine%20of%20the%20Penitent\"&gt;Shrine of the Penitent&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Idol of the Faithful is a item in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", during the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Pilgrimage\"&gt;Pilgrimage&lt;/a&gt;.\" Wearing the idol slows down the player character and greatly reduces their field of vision, along with applying a red filter."}
