{"id": "41364", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41364", "title": "Ifriss the Destroyer", "text": " was a massive saurian &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; that served &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nWhen not dispatched by the Lord of Damnation, Ifriss wallows in the &lt;a href=\"Molten%20Egress\"&gt;Molten Egress&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Skarn's domain&lt;/a&gt;. Magma suffuses its skin, seeping free and starting &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt;s as it tramples through mortal lands. A tongue of flame lolls garishly from its mouth; Ifriss uses it to slurp up the anguished spirit of any creature it &lt;a href=\"burn\"&gt;burn&lt;/a&gt;s alive.\nHistory.\n was summoned into &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Eskara\"&gt;Eskara&lt;/a&gt;, in her final moments. However, Ifriss too was slain by &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; who had slain her.\nHe later reformed in the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt; but was slain by &lt;a href=\"Tassi\"&gt;Tassi&lt;/a&gt; with the help of the hero(es) by using the &lt;a href=\"Iceburn%20Tear\"&gt;Iceburn Tear&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"freeze\"&gt;freeze&lt;/a&gt; him from within.\nAfter reforming once again, he was summoned into the &lt;a href=\"Astral%20Realm\"&gt;Astral Realm&lt;/a&gt; by the &lt;a href=\"Bride%20of%20Hell\"&gt;Bride of Hell&lt;/a&gt; to stop &lt;a href=\"Karshun\"&gt;Karshun&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; from returning to their bodies. Once again, he was killed.\nIn-game.\nIfriss is a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", fought immediately after Eskara in the &lt;a href=\"Unseen%20Lair\"&gt;Unseen Lair&lt;/a&gt;. Ifriss is large and slow, and attacks by swiping its claws, breathing fire, and having fireballs rain down from above. During the fight, &lt;a href=\"Tortured%20Ember\"&gt;Tortured Ember&lt;/a&gt;s will attack the player(s). "}
{"id": "31119", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31119", "title": "Igani Bawe", "text": "The Igani Bawe, otherwise known as the Harvest of Souls, is a form of ritual warfare among the &lt;a href=\"Umbaru\"&gt;Umbaru&lt;/a&gt; tribes. For the Umbaru, there is no greater honor than to take part in the Igani.\nLore.\nThe Igani Bawe is traditionally held in the interval between seasons. It always commences at sunrise, and ends at sundown. The purpose of the Igani is not to slay their fellow Umbaru on the battle itself (this is considered taboo), but rather incapacitate them and capture them to be sacrificed afterwards. When an Umbaru is captured, they embark on the \"Te Wok Nu'cha\", the Final March. When they are sacrificed, their bodies are smeared in ritual oils before their &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; and organs (the latter of which is placed in jars) are offered to the spirits of the &lt;a href=\"Unformed%20Land\"&gt;Unformed Land&lt;/a&gt;. The Umbaru believe that by doing this, they not only nourish the realm for those who will enter it later, but also strengthen their own world (e.g. allowing healthy crops to grow and the seasons to pass). Most Umbaru are prohibited from entering the &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Trance\"&gt;Ghost Trance&lt;/a&gt; during the Igani, as the high priests state it disorientes the &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s of the recently sacrificed tributes.\nIn truth however, the Igani Bawe is unnecessary. Mbwiru Eikura exists regardless of whatever sacrifices the Umbaru make, but it is not utopia either. Two Witch Doctors discovered the truth, &lt;a href=\"Nazeebo\"&gt;Nazeebo&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Benu\"&gt;Benu&lt;/a&gt;. While the former ended up following the &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Fallen Star&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, Benu, who became a spirit, sought to guide the Umbaru away from the needless warfare that they undertook."}
