{"id": "25274", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25274", "title": "Forgotten Soul", "text": "\u00a0is a Legendary crafting material in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", obtained by using the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Haedrig%20Eamon\"&gt;Blacksmith&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0to salvage non-crafted &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; weapons and armor, or &lt;a href=\"set\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; items. \nA &lt;a href=\"Rift%20Guardian\"&gt;Rift Guardian&lt;/a&gt; may also give up one or two of these upon defeat for players in the level range of 61-70 (guaranteed to drop at least one on &lt;a href=\"Torment\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; VII or higher), and &lt;a href=\"Odious%20Collector\"&gt;Odious Collector&lt;/a&gt;s may drop a few as well.\nEach legendary item salvaged will yield 1 Forgotten Soul. An &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Item\"&gt;Ancient Item&lt;/a&gt; rewards 3, and a Primal Ancient Item rewards 15.\nAll Forgotten Souls are &lt;a href=\"Bind%20on%20Account\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0\nPrior to patch 2.3, it was used in crafting\u00a0legendary\u00a0and\u00a0set\u00a0items of level 61-70. In current version of the game, it is only used for &lt;a href=\"enchanting\"&gt;enchanting&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0items, or &lt;a href=\"Kanai%27s%20Cube\"&gt;Kanai's Cube&lt;/a&gt; recipes."}
{"id": "3495", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3495", "title": "Forgotten Temple", "text": "The Forgotten Temple is one of the temples in &lt;a href=\"Upper%20Kurast\"&gt;Upper Kurast&lt;/a&gt;. It can be found by clicking an altar in one of the buildings, revealing a stairway. Inside is a small set of rooms, usually populated by &lt;a href=\"Serpent%20Magus\"&gt;Serpent Magi&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Diver\"&gt;Blood Diver&lt;/a&gt;s, and &lt;a href=\"Bone%20Scarab\"&gt;Bone Scarab&lt;/a&gt;s. According to the quest log, this is one of six temples in which &lt;a href=\"Lam%20Esen%27s%20Tome%20%28item%29\"&gt;Lam Esen's Tome (item)&lt;/a&gt; can be found - however, in reality the tome is always located in the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is one of the area level 85 zones on &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;, and has better drops for this reason. However, it can be quite difficult to fight the particular enemies in there, and the place is very small - hence, it is not often used for &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Find\"&gt;Magic Find&lt;/a&gt;ing."}
{"id": "3749", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3749", "title": "Forgotten Tower", "text": "The Forgotten Tower is a structure that resides within the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Marsh\"&gt;Black Marsh&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nEarly History.\nThe Forgotten Tower is all that remains of an isolated, forested castle located in the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt;. It was once inhabited by &lt;a href=\"the%20Countess\"&gt;the Countess&lt;/a&gt;. For her cruel deeds, she was buried alive, and her castle fell into ruin. By the year &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;1264&lt;/a&gt;, all that remained of the castle was a single solitary tower, looming over the wilderness like a monument to evil. An epic poem was written about the tower, about how much sorrow one could stand there. The tower was not only dangerous due to its state of disrepair; once inside, many succumbed to a vile miasma. Reportedly, several &lt;a href=\"Sisters%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sisters of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt; perished once a staircase collapsed on them. Through means unknown, the Countess emerged, but was slain by a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; inside her tower, and its riches were plundered. \nThe Bloodsworn.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;Six years later&lt;/a&gt;, the Countess returned once again, and resided within the tower. Dwelling within a pool of blood, fed to her by the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Rose\"&gt;Blood Rose&lt;/a&gt;. Because of this, parts of the tower became overgrown with &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Creeper\"&gt;Dark Creeper&lt;/a&gt; vines.\nThe tower became the headquarters of the &lt;a href=\"Bloodsworn\"&gt;Bloodsworn&lt;/a&gt;. The strongest of their number were stationed in the tower, acting as bodyguards to the Countess. The &lt;a href=\"Sisterhood%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sisterhood of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt; launched an assault against the tower, but the attack faltered, such was the ferocity of the Bloodsworn's defense. &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Another group&lt;/a&gt; of heroes came to the tower, slaying any Bloodsworn hat got in their way, though the Bloodsworn engaged in a &lt;a href=\"blood%20magic\"&gt;blood ritual&lt;/a&gt; that the hero(es) failed to stop, which resulted in the resurrection of the Countess. However, the Countess was slain after a long battle.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nThe Forgotten Tower appears as a zone in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". It lies in the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Marsh\"&gt;Black Marsh&lt;/a&gt;, which connects to the &lt;a href=\"Tower%20Cellar\"&gt;Tower Cellar&lt;/a&gt;. Technically the Forgotten Tower only refers to the small area located directly beneath the tower ruins; there are stairs leading up towards the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Marsh\"&gt;Black Marsh&lt;/a&gt; and down into the cellars. The quest is given by the &lt;a href=\"Moldy%20Tome\"&gt;Moldy Tome&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Stony%20Field\"&gt;Stony Field&lt;/a&gt;.\nDiablo Immortal.\nThe Forgotten Tower is revisited in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" as a &lt;a href=\"dungeon%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. The Countess is once again confronted. It differs from its predecessor in that its layout is more open. It is located adjacent to the &lt;a href=\"Sanguine%20Ruins\"&gt;Sanguine Ruins&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "41659", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41659", "title": "Forgotten Tower (Diablo Immortal)", "text": "Forgotten Tower is the second &lt;a href=\"dungeon%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place at the end of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;line, leading on directly from \"&lt;a href=\"Blood%20Resurrection\"&gt;Blood Resurrection&lt;/a&gt;\". Completing the dungeon triggers the \"&lt;a href=\"Delivering%20the%20Shards\"&gt;Delivering the Shards&lt;/a&gt;\" quest.\n&lt;a href=\"Cavern%27s%20Regard\"&gt;Cavern's Regard&lt;/a&gt; drops in this dungeon on &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; V &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt; and above."}
