{"id": "4505", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4505", "title": "Fortitude Rune Word", "text": "Fortitude is the &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Word\"&gt;rune word&lt;/a&gt; \" for &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Body%20Armor\"&gt;body armor&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nIt can be made both in weapon and armor and in both cases it increases both damage and defense, with even more defense stacked on top of that thanks to the auto-cast Chilling Armor. The damage bonus when made in armor makes it a popular choice for any build centered about physical damage or as a &lt;a href=\"Hirelings\"&gt;Hireling&lt;/a&gt; armor.\nNote that \"+X% Enhanced Damage\" only works on weapons; on any other item it's converted to \"Damage +X%\" instead.\nResult Option 1:\nResult Option 2:\n\"Note: The \"+X To Life (Based on Character Level)\" trait varies and may be any one of the following:\""}
{"id": "33180", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33180", "title": "Fortress Ballista", "text": "Fortress Ballista is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Hand%20Crossbows\"&gt;Hand Crossbow&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Hunter\"&gt;Demon Hunter&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", added in patch 2.4.0. It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 70 to drop.\nThe unique affix effect stacks and renews with each application: the potency is added to the remaining one, and then duration refreshes. Any attack suffices regardless of &lt;a href=\"Proc%20Coefficient\"&gt;Proc Coefficient&lt;/a&gt; and number of enemies hit. &lt;a href=\"Ashnagarr%27s%20Blood%20Bracer\"&gt;Ashnagarr's Blood Bracer&lt;/a&gt; does not affect this shield."}
