{"id": "45369", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45369", "title": "Foundling", "text": "s are a type of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nFoundlings are drawn to anything &lt;a href=\"Damage%20Over%20Time%23Burn\"&gt;burning&lt;/a&gt;: torches forges, or flesh. They scurry about heat sources, spreading flames as far as they will go. and taking cruel joy in their effects on others \u2014 effects that leave the foundlings utterly unbothered.\nWhen the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt; invaded &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt;, they summoned legions of demons to besiege &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint%20Keep\"&gt;Stormpoint Keep&lt;/a&gt;. Among these demons were the Foundlings. These foot soldiers carry bags filled with hellish metal, and would not hesitate to hurl balls of red-hot metal at any who cross their path.\nIn-game.\nFoundlings can be found in Stormpoint zone, roaming the &lt;a href=\"Barbican%20Transverse\"&gt;Barbican Transverse&lt;/a&gt;. They are commonly seen under the command of a &lt;a href=\"Castigator%20%28Demon%29\"&gt;Castigator&lt;/a&gt;. They attack at range by throwing balls of hot metal from their bags. These balls &lt;a href=\"damage%20over%20time%23burn\"&gt;burn&lt;/a&gt; the player if they hit. Wherever they land, they form puddles of molten metal that cause &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage."}
