{"id": "38347", "revid": "49826673", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38347", "title": "Fractured Peaks", "text": "Fractured Peaks is a geographic area in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, located south of &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt;, north of &lt;a href=\"Hawezar\"&gt;Hawezar&lt;/a&gt;, and east from the &lt;a href=\"Dry%20Steppes\"&gt;Dry Steppes&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nTeeming with danger, the Fractured Peaks are a frigid wasteland of cold &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;. The Peaks are home to craggy steppes and snow-laden pathways, creating an unforgiving landscape rife with &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s to slay and secrets to discover. Rocky, mountainous surroundings have kept most visitors away from this frozen landscape, which are dotted with crumbling ruins and ancient cathedrals, and a blistering cold saturates the entire region.\nHowever, some call the Peaks home, but they live in a state of constant anxiety; the sense that something is waiting to prey on them when any moment of weakness strikes. When the sun goes down inside the Peaks, the people hunker down in their &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt;s. Any who are caught outside at night are as good as dead, for if they don't fall prey to &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s, the cold will kill them. In the Fractured Peaks, people cling to flickers of light and faith alike.\nGood ale can be a rare commodity in the Fractured Peaks, as arable land for grain is at a premium, and the growing season is short. The best ale found in the peaks is usually imported from the lowlands near &lt;a href=\"Kehjistan\"&gt;Kehjistan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hawezar\"&gt;Hawezar&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Peaks are also the home to a group of religious zealots; devout monks seeking refuge in the isolation of the Peaks to find enlightenment. Their fervant belief in their higher powers keeps them feeling warm and safe during the night, but has left them completely ignorant of the dangers that are slowly, slowly encroaching upon them.\nSnowmelt from the Peaks feeds the swamps of Hawezar. Numerous waterfalls can be seen in the Peaks' south.\nHistory.\nThe history of the Fractured Peaks goes back centuries, if not millennia. At some point, the Peaks was home to a culture (or cultures) that had a faith that &lt;a href=\"Lorath%20Nahr\"&gt;Lorath Nahr&lt;/a&gt; speculated may have been a northern variant of &lt;a href=\"Skatsim\"&gt;Skatsim&lt;/a&gt;. Places of worship were erected to this religion, which in turn, Lorath speculated, were built on even older ruins of a people long since vanished.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Reign%20of%20Enmity\"&gt;Reign of Enmity&lt;/a&gt;, the Peaks came under control of the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt;, which operated out of &lt;a href=\"Kyovashad\"&gt;Kyovashad&lt;/a&gt;. It strove to assert its dominance over the people, to make them more subservient and accountable to the Church. The Peaks' &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt;s paid tithes to the Cathedral, and the Cathedral tore down the old ruins that dotted the Peaks, to erect new structures for their own worship such as the &lt;a href=\"Altars%20of%20Illumination\"&gt;Altars of Illumination&lt;/a&gt;. Shrines dedicated to &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt; were also erected all over the Peaks.\nBy &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; plague was sweeping through the Peaks. It started small; nameless people that no-one would miss, their throats torn open. The Cathedral ignored the killings, even as fear mounted like the bodies. The desperate and the brave fought back against the vampires, but they were too late, either slain, or turned into &lt;a href=\"thrall\"&gt;thrall&lt;/a&gt;s. \nAs winter descended on the Peaks, the &lt;a href=\"Midwinter%20Blight\"&gt;Midwinter Blight&lt;/a&gt; occurred in the Peaks, disrupting any cheer the Peaks' denizens had managed to scrounge for themselves.\nIn-game.\nThe Fractured Peaks are one of the six main geographic areas that can be explored in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It is the starting zone for the game. The region features 25 main quests, along with 25 side quests to complete.\nNotable Locations.\n\"Main article: \nRegions.\nThe Fractured Peaks is divided into the following major regions:"}
{"id": "43291", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43291", "title": "Fractured Plane", "text": "The Fractured Plane is a recurring &lt;a href=\"Season%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;seasonal&lt;/a&gt; event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It will next run in &lt;a href=\"Season%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; 32, from October 18 to 25, 2024.\nLore.\nThe Fractured Plane is a \"shattered reflection of the mind.\" While the Plane appears to be a very real place, it is implied that it appears differently to all those who enter it. Some minds are crushed by such an act.\nAt least two individuals are known to have entered the Plane. The first was &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;, who entered it through the &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Sumina%20Glass\"&gt;Sumina Glass&lt;/a&gt;. Centuries later, this process was repeated by &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;, with the aid of &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"the%20Curator\"&gt;the Curator&lt;/a&gt;. Cain advised them that while entering the Plane carried risk, it could aid them in their fight against &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;. Eventually, they were able to unshackle their mind from the realm.\nGameplay.\nFractured Plane consists of a 12-floor gauntlet that players enter without their usual gear, gems, and skills. Instead, they are provided with a set of pre-selected skills. As players progress, they earn &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20Coin\"&gt;Chaos Coin&lt;/a&gt;s. Unstable &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary Items&lt;/a&gt; drop, and the items received complement the skills the player is given. When the session ends, all the collected gear will vanish.\nEach floor of the Fractured Plane consists of various rooms linked by bridges. Players must beat the current room and then step on one of the circles at the end of a bridge to activate the room on the other side. It is possible to complete all rooms on a floor this way, but the player is free to move on to the next floor after completing the final room that contains a portal.\nThe rooms can be of the following types:\nOne of the rooms is designated as the final room that spawns a portal to the next floor on completion. Warping to the next floor converts all unequipped items into Chaos Coins.\nChaotic Chests containing random gear can be obtained by completing floors 4, 8 and 12.\nIf players make it to the last floor without dying more than five times, they receive a reward. Out of all the Legendary items encountered during the run, players can select six, and out of those six, players will receive one of them at random.\nHistory.\nFractured Plane was introduced in 13. \nBefore the September 21 2023 update, the number of floors was 15 instead of 12, Challenge Rooms had a lower chance of appearing, and Chaotic Chests could only be obtained once.\nCrimson Plane.\nWith the release of the class, a version of Fractured Plane called the &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Plane\"&gt;Crimson Plane&lt;/a&gt; was active, between July 13\u2013August 2, 2023. During this version of the event, the player's build was that of a Blood Knight instead of one for their current class.\nDarkling Plane.\nOn the launch of the &lt;a href=\"Splintered%20Souls\"&gt;Splintered Souls&lt;/a&gt; update, a version of Fractured Plane called The &lt;a href=\"Darkling%20Plane\"&gt;Darkling Plane&lt;/a&gt; was active, between Dec 14-28 2023. During this version of the event, a random was selected for use every time the player started the Fractured Plane.\nThe Deluged Plane.\nOn the launch of the &lt;a href=\"Unending%20Storm\"&gt;Unending Storm&lt;/a&gt; update, a version of Fractured Plane called The Deluged Plane was active, between May 23 and June 13, 2024. During this version of the event, the player's build was that of a &lt;a href=\"Tempest\"&gt;Tempest&lt;/a&gt; instead of one for their current class.\nDevelopment.\nThe Fractured Plane was originally a limited-time event. It was introduced in 2022, and ran again from January 16, 3:00 a.m.\u2013February 6, 2:59 a.m. server time.\nThe event was created to invite players to try new skills and Legendary items that they might not typically use. The developers wanted to provide players with an opportunity to start from scratch to see how well they can play their class no matter the circumstances."}
{"id": "21519", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21519", "title": "Fragment of Destiny", "text": "Fragment of Destiny is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Wands\"&gt;Wand&lt;/a&gt; for the in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 50 to drop.\nPrior to patch 2.4, its bonus to &lt;a href=\"Spectral%20Blade\"&gt;Spectral Blade&lt;/a&gt; was re-rollable. Its damage bonus is multiplicative to other similar effects.\nAs of patch 2.6.10, its unique affix was changed to boost all Signature Spells and . Every successful damaging cast of any Signature spell (&lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shock%20Pulse\"&gt;Shock Pulse&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spectral%20Blade\"&gt;Spectral Blade&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Electrocute\"&gt;Electrocute&lt;/a&gt;) will grant 1 stack of Spectral buff that lasts 6 seconds. The buff stacks up to 10 times and is renewed on each cast. Hydra does not consume stacks, and its damage is determined by the amount of stacks when Hydra attacks, not when it's summoned."}
