{"id": "48268", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48268", "title": "Freedom and Devotion", "text": "Freedom and Devotion is a 1-star &lt;a href=\"legendary%20gem\"&gt;legendary gem&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAwakening.\nFreedom and Devotion requires the following Legendary Gems to activate Resonance set bonuses after &lt;a href=\"Awakening\"&gt;Awakening&lt;/a&gt;:\nThe following Resonance set bonuses can be activated after reaching the needed Resonance from the above gems:\nThe following Legendary Gems require Freedom and Devotion to activate Resonance set bonuses after Awakening:"}
{"id": "3828", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3828", "title": "Freeze", "text": "Freeze\u00a0is a form of &lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It is a more potent (or, in a manner of speaking, extreme) variant of &lt;a href=\"Chill\"&gt;Chill&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe idea is that the target is frozen solid, unable to move and trapped inside the icy tomb, able to do nothing but watch their enemy approaching with the doubtless intention to shatter the frozen victim into pieces. This does not necessarily mean that the victim is going to die: &lt;a href=\"Anya\"&gt;Anya&lt;/a&gt; survived several days of being chained by the freezing curse &lt;a href=\"Nihlathak\"&gt;Nihlathak&lt;/a&gt; has put on her, and recovered instantly when the curse was removed. In both games, a target that was frozen, but not dead, continues to fight normally when they thaw (even though their blood vessels should be torn apart by the blood turned ice).\nFreeze can only happen as a result of unsaved &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Damage\"&gt;Cold Damage&lt;/a&gt; that is specifically stated to be able to Freeze target (while to Chill the victim, any Cold attack will suffice), or a special effect directly stating that it can Freeze an enemy.\nDiablo II.\nThe Frozen target is blue in color and paralyzed completely, and if they die from the freezing attack, or die before the Freeze wears off, they shatter into pieces and &lt;a href=\"Slain%20Monsters%20Rest%20in%20Peace\"&gt;leave no corpse&lt;/a&gt;. This is especially useful when fighting monsters that can be resurrected, such as &lt;a href=\"Fallen\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt;. Freezing enemies is not recommended for &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;s and for most builds connected to corpses.\nThe Frozen victim may not attack, move or cast spells. &lt;a href=\"Act%20Boss\"&gt;Act Boss&lt;/a&gt;es, &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique\"&gt;Super Unique&lt;/a&gt; monsters, &lt;a href=\"Champion\"&gt;Champion&lt;/a&gt; monsters, and other players cannot be frozen; they will, instead, be Chilled. Some items in game have the &lt;a href=\"Half%20Freeze%20Duration\"&gt;Half Freeze Duration&lt;/a&gt; or even &lt;a href=\"Cannot%20Be%20Frozen\"&gt;Cannot Be Frozen&lt;/a&gt; traits, and cold &lt;a href=\"resistance\"&gt;resistance&lt;/a&gt; reduces duration of any Freeze effect. Some monsters, including &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Horror\"&gt;Frozen Horror&lt;/a&gt;s, are entirely immune to Freeze.\nSkills with the Freezing effect are &lt;a href=\"Glacial%20Spike\"&gt;Glacial Spike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Blast\"&gt;Ice Blast&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Armor\"&gt;Frozen Armor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Arrow\"&gt;Ice Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Freezing%20Arrow\"&gt;Freezing Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Phoenix%20Strike\"&gt;Phoenix Strike&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Blades%20of%20Ice\"&gt;Blades of Ice&lt;/a&gt;. Freeze usually has a shorter length than Chill, but is considered a different effect than &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt;.\nFormulas.\nChance of freeze / chill is ( 50 + (AttackerLevel + (B*4) - DefenderLevel) * 5 )%\nB = item bonus (usually is 1). If you use freezing in ranged attack, then AL is decreasing by 6 and chance divides by 3. Duration = (chance - roll) * 2 + 25 frames,\u00a0Duration ranges from 25 frames (1 second) to maximum of 250 frames (10 seconds).\nDiablo Immortal.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", Freeze is normally caused by taking continuous &lt;a href=\"cold\"&gt;cold&lt;/a&gt; damage from specific monsters. A player under this effect is encased in a block of ice and immobilized for seconds. It occurs when a player is under the effect of &lt;a href=\"chill\"&gt;chill&lt;/a&gt;, stacked times.\nSome attacks can instantly freeze the player (eg stalactites in the &lt;a href=\"Cavern%20of%20Echoes\"&gt;Cavern of Echoes&lt;/a&gt;).\nDiablo III.\nIn Diablo III, Freeze is still associated with Cold damage, and can only happen as result of certain Cold skills (mostly ones used by &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;s). The guaranteed shatter on death is gone and replaced with &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt; mechanics: a victim killed by a Cold Critical Hit is shattered into pieces of frozen flesh (or whatever substance they are made of).\nPlayers can be frozen just like monsters, but the duration of all types of duration is reduced by the Crowd Control resistance or by the\u00a0\"reduces duration of control impairing effects\" stat. &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Climbers\"&gt;Ice Climbers&lt;/a&gt; can even make target completely immune to Freeze and &lt;a href=\"Immobilize\"&gt;Immobilize&lt;/a&gt; effects. Being immune to Cold damage (that is, wearing the &lt;a href=\"Talisman%20of%20Aranoch\"&gt;Talisman of Aranoch&lt;/a&gt;) does not prevent the character from being frozen. In addition, most skills with guaranteed Freeze have a limit on how often they can Freeze the same target (usually once every 5 seconds).\n&lt;a href=\"Elites\"&gt;Elite&lt;/a&gt; monsters may have a &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Traits%20%28Diablo%20III%29%23Frozen\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; trait. &lt;a href=\"Izual\"&gt;Izual&lt;/a&gt; also freezes players in combat several times.\n&lt;a href=\"Frostburn%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Frostburn&lt;/a&gt; gloves have a chance to Freeze target with \"any\" Cold damage for 1 second. Another item with an interesting synergy for Freeze is &lt;a href=\"Rimeheart\"&gt;Rimeheart&lt;/a&gt;, which may inflict massive Cold damage on a Frozen enemy.\nDiablo IV.\nIn Diablo IV, Freeze has an additional functionality of applying automatically if enough &lt;a href=\"Chill\"&gt;Chill&lt;/a&gt; effects are stacked on the same target: whenever Chill reaches 100%, the enemy is Frozen.\nAn enemy killed while Frozen is automatically &lt;a href=\"Slain%20Monsters%20Rest%20in%20Peace\"&gt;shattered&lt;/a&gt;, leaving no corpse, regardless of what has killed him in the end."}
{"id": "26911", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26911", "title": "Freeze of Deflection", "text": "Freeze of Deflection\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Shields\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;.\"\u00a0It requires\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a031 to drop.\nThe chance of freezing by the unique Legendary power appears to be roughly 15%."}
{"id": "15969", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15969", "title": "Freezing", "text": "Freezing is a &lt;a href=\"prefix\"&gt;prefix&lt;/a&gt; that can appear on &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic Items&lt;/a&gt;, providing a bonus to &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Spells\"&gt;Cold Spells&lt;/a&gt;.\nStats.\n\"Can appear on\": &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;\"Is available on\": &lt;a href=\"Orbs\"&gt;Orbs&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Staves\"&gt;Staves&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Amulets\"&gt;Amulets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Circlets\"&gt;Circlets&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "2952", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2952", "title": "Freezing Arrow", "text": "Freezing Arrow is an &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"The greatest of the powers attained by those dedicated to &lt;a href=\"Karcheus\"&gt;Karcheus&lt;/a&gt; is the skill to imbue their arrows with the freezing power of a devastating avalanche. Enemies within the impact of a freezing arrow are frozen in their tracks and feel crushing pain, as if a mass of magical ice had toppled onto them. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nFreezing Arrow is the third and last of the Cold-based arrows an &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; can learn. This powerful attack has an area of effect damage and freezing ability, making it useful for dealing with multiple enemies.\nFreezing Arrow is similar to the &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt;' &lt;a href=\"Glacial%20Spike\"&gt;Glacial Spike&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in that it hits and freezes a small area of effect upon impact.\u00a0Other players, bosses, and super uniques will be\u00a0&lt;a href=\"chill\"&gt;chill&lt;/a&gt;ed, not frozen.\u00a0Freezing Arrow can be a bit more powerful however because in addition to the base arrow damage, it also works with &lt;a href=\"Pierce\"&gt;Pierce&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt;, and any equipment modifiers such as &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20Blow\"&gt;Crushing Blow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Open%20Wounds\"&gt;Open Wounds&lt;/a&gt;.\nFreezing Arrow is less useful in &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;, where\u00a0Cold Length Durations are reduced. On Hell the freeze lasts only 0.5 seconds. For a fast bow, however, this is enough to keep most monsters from moving very far. Unlike its fire-based equivalent, &lt;a href=\"Immolation%20Arrow\"&gt;Immolation Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, Freezing Arrow has no &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt;.\nCold damage items have a \"hidden\" chill duration. This chill duration gets added to the freezing time of Freezing Arrow.\u00a0 This additional time is added \"after\" the &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Arrow\"&gt;Ice Arrow&lt;/a&gt; synergy bonus. Stockpiling on small &lt;a href=\"Charms\"&gt;Charms&lt;/a&gt; of cold damage, regardless of the amount of actual damage on the small charm, adds 1 second, which in Hell difficulty is reduced to 0.25 seconds. Ice Arrow, on the other hand, only adds 0.10 seconds per level. Generally, a single small charm of cold damage is worth 10 hard points in Ice Arrow. The cold damage from such items are also added to the \"explosion\" itself, although obtaining external cold damage is much harder than fire.\nSkill Progression.\nFreeze Duration: 2 seconds\nFreeze Radius: 3.3 yards"}
