{"id": "3553", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3553", "title": "Frenzy (Diablo II)", "text": "Frenzy is a &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Although a Barbarian is capable of calculated blows and tactical fighting techniques, it is his fierce passion for battle that distinguishes him in battle. While using this skill, a Barbarian drives more and more force into each successive blow as his anger and bloodlust mounts. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nFrenzy hits an enemy with both weapons, and upon each successful hit, the Barbarian builds charges of Frenzy. For each stack of Frenzy, the Barbarian moves and attacks more quickly. The attack speed bonus applies to all skills while it lasts, not just to Frenzy itself.\nWhile the bonus per stack is fixed, and does not grow with the skill level, maximum bonus does increase, therefore allowing more stacks to be accumulated. The maximum amount of Frenzy one can accumulate is also limited by the relatively low duration of just six seconds (which can be increased by the &lt;a href=\"Increased%20Stamina\"&gt;Increased Stamina&lt;/a&gt; synergy): short duration of the buff makes it very hard to preserve when out of direct combat.\nAs Frenzy has &lt;a href=\"Berserk%20%28Skill%29\"&gt;Berserk&lt;/a&gt; as a synergy, dual-wielding Barbarians can have access to some &lt;a href=\"Magic%20damage\"&gt;Magic damage&lt;/a&gt; after enough points have been allocated, allowing them to destroy &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Immune\"&gt;Immune&lt;/a&gt; monsters within a reasonable amount of time while not suffering the drawback of destroying their\u00a0&lt;a href=\"defense\"&gt;defense&lt;/a&gt;s to the point of suffering from almost every hit.\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 3\nDuration: 6 seconds"}
{"id": "9256", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9256", "title": "Frenzy (Diablo III)", "text": "Frenzy is a Primary \u00a0&lt;a href=\"Skill%20Trees\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt;, based on the \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" skill &lt;a href=\"Frenzy%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;of the same name&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nLike , Frenzy hits a single enemy, but each damaging hit increases the attack speed (for this skill only, not for other skills), stacking up to a total bonus of .\nWhen fully stacked, Frenzy compensates its low damage with the ability to deliver \"very\" rapid strikes, especially when &lt;a href=\"Dual-Wielding\"&gt;Dual-Wielding&lt;/a&gt;, without sacrificing raw damage. If combined with a high degree of &lt;a href=\"Life%20on%20Hit\"&gt;Life on Hit&lt;/a&gt; and possibly the\u00a0 known as , Frenzy grants the Barbarian the ability to &lt;a href=\"heal\"&gt;heal&lt;/a&gt; their injuries greater than what the other Primary skills would be able to do."}
