{"id": "38810", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38810", "title": "Frenzy (Diablo IV)", "text": "Frenzy\u00a0is a Basic skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", a remake of the classic &lt;a href=\"Frenzy\"&gt;Frenzy&lt;/a&gt; skills.\nIn-game.\nAs before, successfully hitting with Frenzy applies a brief, but stacking (up to 3 times) &lt;a href=\"attack%20speed\"&gt;attack speed&lt;/a&gt; increase. Requires two &lt;a href=\"One-Handed\"&gt;One-Handed&lt;/a&gt; weapons to be equipped and switches to those when used. Damage listed in the tooltip is delivered in two separate hits, but each cast always makes two of them anyway.\nCounts as Berserker skill."}
