{"id": "54413", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54413", "title": "Frenzy (monster skill)", "text": "Frenzy (not to be mistaken for &lt;a href=\"Minion%20Frenzy\"&gt;Minion Frenzy&lt;/a&gt;) is a skill used by some &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s. The monster buffs themselves, temporarily increasing their &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Damage\"&gt;Damage&lt;/a&gt; and\u2014at times, &lt;a href=\"Movement%20Speed\"&gt;Movement Speed&lt;/a&gt;. This skill is preceded by a short animation, and is indicated by an aura or color change. In \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" it is used by &lt;a href=\"Night%20Howler\"&gt;Night Howler&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Ashen%20Marauder\"&gt;Ashen Marauder&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Scavenger\"&gt;Scavenger&lt;/a&gt;s. "}
{"id": "22589", "revid": "5210039", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22589", "title": "Frenzy Barb", "text": ""}
{"id": "9253", "revid": "52534049", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9253", "title": "Frenzy Barbarian", "text": "Frenzy Barbarian is one of the main and best known builds for the &lt;a href=\"class\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". These warriors utilize two weapons at once and swing them with much power. Specializing in Frenzy means dual-wielding weapons, attacking and moving really quickly, and doing heavy damage to every enemy within arm's reach.\nAdvantages and Disadvantages.\nAdvantages\nDisadvantages\nStat Point Allocation.\nStrength: Enough to equip desired gear.\nDexterity: Enough to equip desired weapons.\nVitality: Everything else here.\nEnergy: This should be left at its base value.\nEquipment.\nFor the Secondary Weapon, pick another one of the above. It is not recommended use two of the same weapon, as the properties, particularly the auras on many of these weapons, would be redundant.\nAdditional charms with +life will also do. Combat Charms, although attractive looking, add only 7% Attack Rating and 3% extra damage, so one could trade those to a build that would benefit more from them. Resistance charms can also be a consideration.\nTips and Tricks.\nPlayer vs. Player.\nDueling is difficult as a Frenzy Barb because you have to get close to your enemy and physically attack them first, one swing at a time. The only way that is notably simple to duel as a frenzy barb is to frenzy on monsters in the wilderness ahead of time to build up damage and attack speed."}
