{"id": "9471", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9471", "title": "Frost Charger", "text": "Frost Chargers are yet another variation of the &lt;a href=\"Horned%20Demon\"&gt;Horned Demon&lt;/a&gt; and can be found on the mid levels of the Caves. \nFrost Chargers have developed an immunity to &lt;a href=\"Magic\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and resistance to , and these stats, in addition to their increased health pool and attack, make them deadly foes to deal with. \nThey have &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; resistance in the lore, but it doesn't exist in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "46234", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46234", "title": "Frost Horror", "text": "s are a group of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s that have roamed the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Arreat&lt;/a&gt; since the &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Destruction\"&gt;Lord of Destruction&lt;/a&gt; laid waste to it.\nLore.\ns are born intangible, and fashion their bodies and weapons from their environment. They begin at roughly human sized, and can grow to immense sizes when powerful enough. The bones of frost horrors are littered with fractures and jagged spurs. All variants of frost horrors have affinity for manipulating &lt;a href=\"cold\"&gt;cold&lt;/a&gt;, and normally carry weapons partly or fully made from ice. Some frost horrors fight with weapons using a mockery of fighting styles, while others use &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;; specifically of the cold element.\ns were part of Baal's army when he attacked Arreat and some even rose to prominence.\nIn-game.\nFrost Horrors are featured in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", and can be found at the &lt;a href=\"Plains%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Plains of Blood&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;. Each of their attack &lt;a href=\"chill\"&gt;chill&lt;/a&gt;s the player, and the more powerful versions can &lt;a href=\"freeze\"&gt;freeze&lt;/a&gt; the player."}
{"id": "46235", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46235", "title": "Frost Horror Overlord", "text": "s are a type of &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Horror\"&gt;Frost Horror&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are the more powerful versions of the &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Horror%20Shardmage\"&gt;shardmages&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nA sufficiently powerful frost horror shardmage becomes an overlord after fashioning a staff from the skull and spine of a comrade. Overlords direct the deployment of lesser horrors, and their ability to manipulate &lt;a href=\"cold\"&gt;cold&lt;/a&gt; grows ever stronger, manifesting in waves of frost that &lt;a href=\"freeze\"&gt;freeze&lt;/a&gt; squads of warriors where they stand.\nPowerful overlords are called &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Horror\"&gt;Elder Horror&lt;/a&gt;s.\nIn-game.\ns can be found at the &lt;a href=\"Plains%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Plains of Blood&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;. In addition to the abilities of a shard mage, they can control weaker frost horrors and summon a &lt;a href=\"chill\"&gt;chill&lt;/a&gt;y wind that &lt;a href=\"freeze\"&gt;freeze&lt;/a&gt;s the player on continued exposure."}
{"id": "45777", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45777", "title": "Frost Horror Sadist", "text": "s are a type of &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Horror\"&gt;Frost Horror&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", in the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nSome immense frost horrors rose to prominence in &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;'s army for their ability to win battles through fear alone. Sadists swing &lt;a href=\"ice\"&gt;ice&lt;/a&gt;-spiked boulders like flails, and crush foes underfoot as they fight. In victory, a sadist decapitates their most renowned enemy, then impales the head on its spines, creating a record of triumph for all to see."}
{"id": "48161", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48161", "title": "Frost Horror Shardmage", "text": "s are basic variant of &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Horror\"&gt;Frost Horror&lt;/a&gt;s that dabble in &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\ns are &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic enemies featured in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are commonly found at the &lt;a href=\"Plains%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Plains of Blood&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;. They attack by shooting &lt;a href=\"ice\"&gt;icicles&lt;/a&gt; at the player. Their attacks have a slight &lt;a href=\"chill\"&gt;chill&lt;/a&gt; effect."}
{"id": "46233", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46233", "title": "Frost Horror Slasher", "text": "s are a type of &lt;a href=\"Frost%20Horror\"&gt;Frost Horror&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThese malformed wretches are born intangible, and fashion their bodies and their weapons from their environments. As onetime subjects of the Lord of Destruction, &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;, the modern frost horrors arose in the &lt;a href=\"Plains%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Plains of Blood&lt;/a&gt;, where they climb half- formed from piles of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Arreat's&lt;/a&gt; dead, and fight in a mockery of the twin-bladed style.\nIn-game.\ns can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Plains%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Plains of Blood&lt;/a&gt; and around the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%27s%20Graveyard\"&gt;Ancient's Graveyard&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;. They attack with &lt;a href=\"ice\"&gt;ice&lt;/a&gt; daggers that &lt;a href=\"chill\"&gt;chill&lt;/a&gt; the player."}
