{"id": "5206", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5206", "title": "Frozen Horror", "text": "The Frozen Horror is a creature completely made of ice. It can be encountered inside the ice caves in &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Destruction%20%28Act%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; of \".\"\nLore.\nNot all of &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;\u2019s minions have form. Many of his demons are completely intangible on the mortal plane. However, this makes attacking helpless mortals impossible. The ice in the caves of &lt;a href=\"Mt.%20Arreat\"&gt;Mt. Arreat&lt;/a&gt; is a limitless resource for these demons to take their form from.\nIn-Game.\nEven though they are demon spirits encased in ice, they are counted as &lt;a href=\"Animals\"&gt;Animals&lt;/a&gt;. They usually appear in large numbers, moving slowly and attacking with their claws at relatively long range in comparison to other melee attacks. If you get too close they will try to freeze you using a blast similar to the druid's &lt;a href=\"Arctic%20Blast\"&gt;Arctic Blast&lt;/a&gt; skill. This can be dangerous for those not immune to freezing. Frozen Creepers will always shatter and dissolve when they die, leaving no corpse behind. \nAll Frozen Horror types would gain speed in &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; upon being chilled, but it can't normally be seen because of their high &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; Immunity. "}
