{"id": "3527", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3527", "title": "Frozen Tundra", "text": "The Frozen Tundra is located in the &lt;a href=\"Dreadlands\"&gt;Dreadlands&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nDespite the adverse conditions in the Frozen Tundra, many creatures inhabit these lands. They all have their own way to resist the cold.\nSince the destruction of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Mount Arreat&lt;/a&gt;, the Frozen Tundra has been inhabited by scattered tribes, and &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20Spirit\"&gt;spirits&lt;/a&gt; of the fallen haunt the region. Despite &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;'s defeat at Arreat, the remnants of his &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Destruction\"&gt;army&lt;/a&gt; remained. Only the Barbarian tribes were able to keep these remnants at bay, but they were scattered and isolated. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero/group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; came to the Tundra. In the knowledge that the Barbarians had to live united or die divided, they sought to rally the tribes against their common foe. Otherwise, &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;hell&lt;/a&gt; would break loose once more.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nThe tundra is a zone in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", between the &lt;a href=\"Glacial%20Trail\"&gt;Glacial Trail&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Ancients%27%20Way\"&gt;The Ancients' Way&lt;/a&gt;. The area is divided by numerous fortifications. Somewhere within it is the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Pit\"&gt;Infernal Pit&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnlike the wilderness areas close to the city, this area is almost entirely covered by white snow. This can cause some difficulty in picking out other white-colored (or bright) missile attacks like charged bolts or blood stars. Beware when facing monsters that can fire such missiles.\nDevelopment.\nThe area is called \"Tundra Wastelands\" in files.\nDiablo Immortal.\nThe Frozen Tundra features in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is one of the game's major areas."}
