{"id": "32066", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32066", "title": "Garan", "text": "Garan, Corrupted Elder of the Unclean, is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"The%20Unclean\"&gt;Unclean One&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Ruins of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nGaran can randomly spawn in the Ruins of Sescheron. It appears that he &lt;a href=\"dual-wield\"&gt;dual-wield&lt;/a&gt;s two &lt;a href=\"Limb%20Cleaver\"&gt;Limb Cleaver&lt;/a&gt;s.\nLike other Barbarian cannibals, Garan has very high melee damage, huge &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; pool and moves very quickly. In addition, he has &lt;a href=\"Furious%20Charge\"&gt;Furious Charge&lt;/a&gt; and skills, the latter not being channeled, but rather activated for 6 seconds, not impairing normal attack.\nHe starts combat on the ceiling, falling on player from above, so it is impossible to ambush him.\nGaran can be assigned as a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt;, in which case the secondary objective is to kill 50 enemies."}
